(16, 3, 88, 'Cairo to Luxor Tour 5 Days \\ Private tour', 'Spend 5 days exploring attractions along the famous Nile river in a private guided tour of Egypt throughout the ages. Visit the iconic Giza Pyramids and the Sphinx, tour the Egyptian Museum, explore Coptic Cairo, and shop at Khan Al Khalili in Islamic Cairo. After your adventures in Egypt‚Äôs capital, you‚Äôll head south to Luxor, where you‚Äôll see Hatshepsut Temple, the Valley of the Kings, Karnak Temples and Luxor Temple.', '<div class=\"full_itinerary_box\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 10px; border: 1px solid rgb(235, 235, 235); font-family: Avenir, sans-serif; border-radius: 10px; background-color: rgb(253, 253, 253); float: left; width: 566.656px; position: relative; font-size: 14px;\">\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_title toggled\" id=\"itinerary_title_1\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 20px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; float: left; width: 544.656px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); cursor: pointer;\">\r\n<h2 style=\"font-style:inherit\">Day 1: Arrival in Cairo - Welcome to Egypt</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_desc\" id=\"itinerary_desc_1\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 34px 20px; padding: 20px 0px 0px; border-width: 1px 0px 0px; border-top-style: solid; border-right-style: initial; border-bottom-style: initial; border-left-style: initial; border-top-color: rgb(225, 225, 225); border-right-color: initial; border-bottom-color: initial; border-left-color: initial; border-image: initial; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 15px;\">\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Welcome to Cairo, Egypt (around the clock)<br />\r\nYour tour manager will meet and assist you at Cairo International<a href=\"https://www.memphistours.com/Egypt/WikiTravel/General/wiki/Cairo-International-Airport\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(8, 149, 255); text-decoration-line: none !important;\">&nbsp;</a>Airport(Arrival<a href=\"https://www.memphistours.com/Egypt/WikiTravel/General/wiki/Arrival-procedures-at-Cairo-International-Airport\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(8, 149, 255); text-decoration-line: none !important;\">&nbsp;</a>Procedures) and will then escort you to your hotel in an air-conditioned deluxe vehicle. At the hotel, your tour manager will assist you with a smooth check-in and review your vacation itinerary to establish and confirm pick-up times for each tour. Overnight in Cairo.<br />\r\n<strong>Welcome Drink</strong></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"full_itinerary_box\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 10px; border: 1px solid rgb(235, 235, 235); font-family: Avenir, sans-serif; border-radius: 10px; background-color: rgb(253, 253, 253); float: left; width: 566.656px; position: relative; font-size: 14px;\">\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_title toggled\" id=\"itinerary_title_2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 20px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; float: left; width: 544.656px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); cursor: pointer;\">\r\n<h2 style=\"font-style:inherit\">Day 2: Pyramids and Cairo Sightseeing</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_desc\" id=\"itinerary_desc_2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 34px 20px; padding: 20px 0px 0px; border-width: 1px 0px 0px; border-top-style: solid; border-right-style: initial; border-bottom-style: initial; border-left-style: initial; border-top-color: rgb(225, 225, 225); border-right-color: initial; border-bottom-color: initial; border-left-color: initial; border-image: initial; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 15px;\">\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">After breakfast you will be accompanied by your personal guide to Giza<a href=\"https://www.memphistours.com/Egypt/Egypt-Wikis/Egypt-Pyramids/wiki/Giza-Necropolis\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(8, 149, 255); text-decoration-line: none !important;\">&nbsp;</a>Plateau&nbsp;to visit one of the seven wonders of the ancient world: the Great<a href=\"https://www.memphistours.com/Egypt/Egypt-Wikis/Egypt-Destinations/wiki/Egypt-Pyramids\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(8, 149, 255); text-decoration-line: none !important;\">&nbsp;</a>Pyramids&nbsp;of Cheops, Chefren, and Mykerinus, along with the famous Sphinx&nbsp;and Valley<a href=\"https://www.memphistours.com/Egypt/WikiTravel/Attractions-Cairo/wiki/Valley-Temple\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(8, 149, 255); text-decoration-line: none !important;\">&nbsp;</a>Temple. Then, head out to the Egyptian<a href=\"https://www.memphistours.com/Egypt/WikiTravel/Attractions-Cairo/wiki/Egyptian-Museum-Ground-floor\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(8, 149, 255); text-decoration-line: none !important;\">&nbsp;</a>Museum, where the treasures of the boy King<a href=\"https://www.memphistours.com/Egypt/Egypt-Wikis/Egypt-History/wiki/Tutankhamoun\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(8, 149, 255); text-decoration-line: none !important;\">&nbsp;</a>Tutankhamen&nbsp;await you. Continue to Khan El<a href=\"https://www.memphistours.com/Egypt/Egypt-Wikis/Cairo-Attractions/wiki/Khan-El-Khalili\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(8, 149, 255); text-decoration-line: none !important;\">&nbsp;</a>Khalili, Cairo&rsquo;s oldest and most alluring bazaar. Back to hotel and overnight in Cairo.<br />\r\n<strong>Meals:</strong>&nbsp;Breakfast, Lunch.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"full_itinerary_box\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 10px; border: 1px solid rgb(235, 235, 235); font-family: Avenir, sans-serif; border-radius: 10px; background-color: rgb(253, 253, 253); float: left; width: 566.656px; position: relative; font-size: 14px;\">\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_title toggled\" id=\"itinerary_title_3\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 20px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; float: left; width: 544.656px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); cursor: pointer;\">\r\n<h2 style=\"font-style:inherit\">Day 3: Fly from Cairo to Luxor - Valley of the Kings Tour</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_desc\" id=\"itinerary_desc_3\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 34px 20px; padding: 20px 0px 0px; border-width: 1px 0px 0px; border-top-style: solid; border-right-style: initial; border-bottom-style: initial; border-left-style: initial; border-top-color: rgb(225, 225, 225); border-right-color: initial; border-bottom-color: initial; border-left-color: initial; border-image: initial; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 15px;\">\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">After breakfast, you&rsquo;ll check out from the hotel in the morning and then transfer to Cairo Airport for your flight to Luxor, and then taken to your hotel to check in. You&rsquo;ll proceed to visit the Royal Cemetery for 62 Pharaohs, the Valley of The<a href=\"https://www.memphistours.com/Egypt/Egypt-Wikis/Luxor-Attractions/wiki/Valley-of-the-Kings\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(8, 149, 255); text-decoration-line: none !important;\">&nbsp;</a>Kings, then to mortuary Temple of Queen<a href=\"https://www.memphistours.com/Egypt/Egypt-Wikis/Egypt-History/wiki/Queen-Hatshepsut\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(8, 149, 255); text-decoration-line: none !important;\">&nbsp;</a>Hatshepsut, which was built by the architects of the New Kingdom during the 15th century BC. Travel on to the Colossi of<a href=\"https://www.memphistours.com/Egypt/Egypt-Wikis/Luxor-Attractions/wiki/Colossi-of-Memnon\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(8, 149, 255); text-decoration-line: none !important;\">&nbsp;</a>Memnon. You&rsquo;ll then transfer to your hotel in Luxor, where you&rsquo;ll stay overnight. Optional trip to a sound &amp; light show at Karnak Temples.<br />\r\n<strong>Meals:</strong>&nbsp;Breakfast, Lunch</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Flight Time Approx: Cairo to Luxor 06:00 - 07:00</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"full_itinerary_box\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 10px; border: 1px solid rgb(235, 235, 235); font-family: Avenir, sans-serif; border-radius: 10px; background-color: rgb(253, 253, 253); float: left; width: 566.656px; position: relative; font-size: 14px;\">\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_title toggled\" id=\"itinerary_title_4\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 20px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; float: left; width: 544.656px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); cursor: pointer;\">\r\n<h2 style=\"font-style:inherit\">Day 4: Luxor Sightseeing and Flight to Cairo</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_desc\" id=\"itinerary_desc_4\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 34px 20px; padding: 20px 0px 0px; border-width: 1px 0px 0px; border-top-style: solid; border-right-style: initial; border-bottom-style: initial; border-left-style: initial; border-top-color: rgb(225, 225, 225); border-right-color: initial; border-bottom-color: initial; border-left-color: initial; border-image: initial; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 15px;\">\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">After breakfast, you&rsquo;ll explore the towering Karnak<a href=\"https://www.memphistours.com/Egypt/Egypt-Wikis/Luxor-Attractions/wiki/Karnak-Temple\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(8, 149, 255); text-decoration-line: none !important;\">&nbsp;</a>Temples&nbsp;and the famed Luxor<a href=\"https://www.memphistours.com/Egypt/Egypt-Wikis/Luxor-Attractions/wiki/Luxor-Temple\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(8, 149, 255); text-decoration-line: none !important;\">&nbsp;</a>Temple. After your trip to the temples, you will be driven to the Luxor airport for your flight to Cairo, where you will be met and assisted at the airport and taken to your hotel. Overnight in Cairo.<br />\r\n<strong>Meals:</strong>&nbsp;Breakfast, Lunch</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Flight Time Approx: Luxor to Cairo 22:00 - 23:00</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"full_itinerary_box\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 10px; border: 1px solid rgb(235, 235, 235); font-family: Avenir, sans-serif; border-radius: 10px; background-color: rgb(253, 253, 253); float: left; width: 566.656px; position: relative; font-size: 14px;\">\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_title toggled\" id=\"itinerary_title_5\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 20px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; float: left; width: 544.656px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); cursor: pointer;\">\r\n<h2 style=\"font-style:inherit\">Day 5: Cairo - Fly Back Home</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_desc\" id=\"itinerary_desc_5\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 34px 20px; padding: 20px 0px 0px; border-width: 1px 0px 0px; border-top-style: solid; border-right-style: initial; border-bottom-style: initial; border-left-style: initial; border-top-color: rgb(225, 225, 225); border-right-color: initial; border-bottom-color: initial; border-left-color: initial; border-image: initial; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 15px;\">\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Enjoy breakfast at your hotel in Cairo, after which you will be transferred to Cairo International Airport for departure.<br />\r\n<strong>Meals:</strong>&nbsp;Breakfast.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', '28908023_1547745711947254_1433027978_n (1).jpg', '67968389_2118271291812525_8476687789147029504_n.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '550.00', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Meet and greet service by our representatives upon your airport arrival.</li>\r\n	<li>Assistance with guest relations during your stay.</li>\r\n	<li>All transfers in a private air-conditioned vehicle.</li>\r\n	<li>Domestic flights (Cairo / Luxor / Cairo).</li>\r\n	<li>Accommodation in Cairo for 3 nights, including daily breakfast.</li>\r\n	<li>Accommodation in Luxor for 1 night, including daily breakfast.</li>\r\n	<li>All sightseeing tours as mentioned in the itinerary (private tours).</li>\r\n	<li>Local English speaking tour guide.</li>\r\n	<li>Entrance fees to all sites mentioned on the itinerary.</li>\r\n	<li>All meals mentioned on the itinerary.</li>\r\n	<li>Bottled water during outings outside of hotel or cruise ship.</li>\r\n	<li>Portage as needed.</li>\r\n	<li>30 minutes of local calling (5 minutes international) and a mobile phone loaned for the length of your stay or an Egyptian sim card for your unlocked mobile device.</li>\r\n	<li>All service charges and taxes.</li>\r\n</ul>', '<ul>\r\n	<li>International airfare.</li>\r\n	<li>Entry visa to Egypt.</li>\r\n	<li>Any optional tours.</li>\r\n	<li>Personal spending.</li>\r\n	<li>Tipping.</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL, 'no', '5', NULL, 'egypt-luxor-tour-packages-egypt-tours', NULL, NULL, '2019-08-18 15:09:13', '2019-09-02 11:48:32'),
(17, 3, 88, '8 Days Pyramids & Nile cruise by Air', 'Experience Egypt with Nile Cruise Holiday. Stop in Cairo to visit the Giza Pyramids and the Egyptian Museum before flying to Luxor to embark on a Nile cruise. See impressive ruins and beautiful scenery between Luxor and Aswan on a luxurious 5-day cruise before returning to Cairo to depart.', '<h3>Day 1: Arrival Cairo &ndash; Welcome to land of the Pharaoh&rsquo;s</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Welcome to Cairo, Egypt (Around The Clock)<br />\r\nYour tour manager will meet and assist you at Cairo International Airport (Arrival procedures) and then he will escort you to the hotel by exclusive air-conditioned deluxe vehicle. At hotel the tour manager will assist with a smooth check-in and review your holiday itinerary with you to establish and confirm pick-up times for each tour. Overnight in Cairo.<br />\r\nWelcome Drink</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Day 2: Pyramids and Cairo Sightseeing</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Breakfast at your hotel in Cairo and then met by your personal guide who will accompany you to Giza Plateau to visit one of the seven wonders of the ancient world, the Great Pyramids of Cheops, Chephren and Mykerinus, famous Sphinx, and Valley temple facing the great statue. Lunch at a good quality local restaurant. Then transfer to enjoy the Egyptian Museum, Treasures room for the child king Tutankhamen. Continue to Coptic Cairo to visit the Hanging Church and Ben Ezra Synagogue. Continue driving to Islamic Cairo, where you will be able to explore Khan El Khalili, Cairo&rsquo;s old bazaar.. Back to your hotel. Overnight in Cairo.<br />\r\nMeals: Breakfast, Lunch</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Day 3: Fly Cairo to Luxor &ndash; Nile Cruise Tour</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Check out from hotel in the morning then transfer to Cairo Airport for a flight with EGYPTAIR to Luxor where you will be met and assisted, then taken by an air-conditioned vehicle to board your Egypt Nile cruise to check in. After lunch on board, enjoy a visit to the impressive Karnak Temples and Luxor Temple. Dinner and overnight on board Nile cruise.<br />\r\nMeals: Breakfast, Lunch, Dinner</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Day 4: Luxor Nile Cruise Excursions</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>After breakfast on your Nile cruise, take an excursion to the royal cemetery for 62 Pharaohs, Valley of the Kings, then to mortuary Temple of Queen Hatshepsut, which was built by the architects of the New Kingdom Pharaoh Hatshepsut in the 15th century BC. Head to the Colossi of Memnon. After lunch, you will sail to Edfu enjoying a leisurely dinner on board. Overnight on board Nile Cruise.<br />\r\nMeals: Breakfast, Lunch, Dinner</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Day 5: Edfu and Kom Ombo Temples</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>After breakfast on Nile Cruise, visit the well-preserved Ptolemaic Temple dedicated to Horus at Edfu. Sail to Kom Ombo to see the unique Temple of Sobek, dedicated to Sobek the crocodile god, and Horus the falcon-headed god.Have your lunch on board. Continue sailing to Aswan. Dinner and overnight on board your Nile Cruise.<br />\r\nMeals: Breakfast, Lunch, Dinner</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Day 6: Aswan Nile Cruise Tours</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>After breakfast on Nile cruise, enjoy a day&rsquo;s sightseeing in Aswan. Start with the High Dam and the largest known ancient obelisk, located in the northern region of the stone quarries of ancient Egypt, the Unfinished Obelisk, proceeding to the beautiful Temple of Philae, which is devoted to the two goddesses Isis and Hathor. Dinner and overnight on board deluxe Nile Cruise.<br />\r\nMeals: Breakfast, Lunch, Dinner</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Day 7: Fly Aswan to Cairo</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Disembark from your Nile cruise after breakfast, then transfer to Aswan Airport for your return to Cairo where you will be met and assisted at the airport then taken to your hotel. Overnight in Cairo.<br />\r\nMeals: Breakfast</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Day 8: Cairo &ndash; Fly Back Home</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Breakfast at the hotel with free time at your leisure, then you will be transferred to Cairo International Airport for your final departure.<br />\r\nMeals: Breakfast</p>', '68474623_1572807952849965_2846593474977857536_n.jpg', '69185306_1079961848869264_1441317468927688704_n.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1050.00', '<p><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Meet and greet service by our representatives at airports</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Assistance of our guest relations during your stay</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">All transfers to/from airport &amp; hotel by a private air-conditioned vehicle</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Domestic flight ticket Cairo to Luxor and Aswan to Cairo by Egyptair</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Accommodation for 3 nights in Cairo including daily breakfast</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Accommodation for 4 nights on 05 star Superior Nile Cruise on full board</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">All sightseeing tours in Cairo (Private Tours)</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">All sightseeing tours on the cruise (private tours)</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">English-speaking tour guide during your trips</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Entrance fees to all sites as indicated on the itinerary</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Meals at hotel, Nile cruise and during your tours as mentioned in the itinerary</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Bottled water during the trip</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Portage when needed</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">30 minutes of local calling sim card for the length of your stay or an Egyptian sim card for your unlocked mobile device</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">All service charges and taxes</span></p>', '<div class=\"scroll_pane_new\" id=\"overview\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-family: Avenir, sans-serif; width: 566.656px; float: left; font-size: 14px;\">\r\n<div class=\"program_box_data\" id=\"exclude\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 15px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; width: 566.656px; float: left;\">\r\n<div style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit;\">\r\n<div style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit;\">\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>International Airfare</li>\r\n	<li>Entry visa to Egypt</li>\r\n	<li>Any optional tours</li>\r\n	<li>Personal spendings</li>\r\n	<li>Tipping</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"scroll_pane_new\" id=\"itinerary\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 20px 0px 0px; border: 0px; font-family: Avenir, sans-serif; width: 566.656px; float: left; font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;</div>', NULL, 'no', '5', NULL, 'pyramids-nile-cruise-egypt-tours-packages', NULL, NULL, '2019-08-18 19:54:38', '2019-09-02 12:01:09'),
(18, 3, 88, '8 Days Cairo & Nile Cruise by Sleeper Train', 'Discover Egypt‚Äôs captivating pharaonic history through an exciting tour across the country over river and rail. This cheaper alternative to our popular Egypt by Air tour features the same activities, but you‚Äôll do some traveling via sleeper train instead of taking domestic flights. You‚Äôll visit the Great Pyramids and witness the astounding beauty of the last remaining of the original seven wonders of the ancient world. After exploring the majesty of Cairo‚Äôs past and present, you‚Äôll board a sleeper train headed southward to Aswan. A luxury cruise ship awaits you, and you‚Äôll witness the monuments and natural beauty of southern Egypt in style. Spend three days sailing and sightseeing between Aswan and Luxor before heading back to Cairo via train.', '<div class=\"full_itinerary_box\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 10px; border: 1px solid rgb(235, 235, 235); font-family: Avenir, sans-serif; border-radius: 10px; float: left; width: 700px; position: relative; font-size: 14px; line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(253, 253, 253);\">\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_title\" id=\"itinerary_title_1\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 20px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; float: left; width: 678px; color: rgb(92, 94, 98); cursor: pointer;\">\r\n<h2 style=\"font-style:inherit\">Day 1: Arrival in Cairo - Welcome to the Land of the Pharaohs</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_desc\" id=\"itinerary_desc_1\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 34px 20px; padding: 20px 0px 0px; border-width: 1px 0px 0px; border-top-style: solid; border-top-color: rgb(225, 225, 225); font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 15px;\">\r\n<div style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit;\">Your tour manager will meet and assist you at Cairo International<a href=\"https://www.memphistours.com/Egypt/WikiTravel/General/wiki/Cairo-International-Airport\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; color: rgb(8, 149, 255); text-decoration: none !important; background-color: transparent;\">&nbsp;</a>Airport&nbsp;(Arrival<a href=\"https://www.memphistours.com/Egypt/WikiTravel/General/wiki/Arrival-procedures-at-Cairo-International-Airport\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; color: rgb(8, 149, 255); text-decoration: none !important; background-color: transparent;\">&nbsp;</a>Procedures) and will then escort you to your hotel in an air-conditioned deluxe vehicle. At the hotel, your tour manager will assist you with a smooth check-in and review your budget vacation itinerary with you to establish and confirm pick-up times for each tour. Overnight in Cairo.<br />\r\nWelcome drink included</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"full_itinerary_box\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 10px; border: 1px solid rgb(235, 235, 235); font-family: Avenir, sans-serif; border-radius: 10px; float: left; width: 700px; position: relative; font-size: 14px; line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(253, 253, 253);\">\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_title\" id=\"itinerary_title_2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 20px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; float: left; width: 678px; color: rgb(92, 94, 98); cursor: pointer;\">\r\n<h2 style=\"font-style:inherit\">Day 2: Pyramids and Cairo Sightseeing - Train to Aswan</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_desc\" id=\"itinerary_desc_2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 34px 20px; padding: 20px 0px 0px; border-width: 1px 0px 0px; border-top-style: solid; border-top-color: rgb(225, 225, 225); font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 15px;\">\r\n<div style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit;\">Enjoy your breakfast at the hotel in Cairo before checking out, then your personal tour guide will accompany you to Giza Plateau to visit one of the seven wonders of the ancient world: the Great<a href=\"https://www.memphistours.com/Egypt/Egypt-Wikis/Egypt-Destinations/wiki/Egypt-Pyramids\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; color: rgb(8, 149, 255); text-decoration: none !important; background-color: transparent;\">&nbsp;</a>Pyramids&nbsp;of Cheops, Chefren, and Mykerinus, along with the Famous<a href=\"https://www.memphistours.com/Egypt/WikiTravel/Attractions-Cairo/wiki/Sphinx-in-Ancient-Egypt\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; color: rgb(8, 149, 255); text-decoration: none !important; background-color: transparent;\">&nbsp;</a>Sphinx&nbsp;and Valley<a href=\"https://www.memphistours.com/Egypt/WikiTravel/Attractions-Cairo/wiki/Valley-Temple\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; color: rgb(8, 149, 255); text-decoration: none !important; background-color: transparent;\">&nbsp;</a>Temple. Then, head out to the Egyptian<a href=\"https://www.memphistours.com/Egypt/Egypt-Wikis/Cairo-Attractions/wiki/Egyptian-Museum-Cairo\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; color: rgb(8, 149, 255); text-decoration: none !important; background-color: transparent;\">&nbsp;</a>Museum&nbsp;where the treasures of the boy king Tutankhamen await you. Continue to Islamic<a href=\"https://www.memphistours.com/Egypt/Egypt-Wikis/Cairo-Attractions/wiki/Islamic-Cairo\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; color: rgb(8, 149, 255); text-decoration: none !important; background-color: transparent;\">&nbsp;</a>Cairo, where you will be able to explore Khan El<a href=\"https://www.memphistours.com/Egypt/Egypt-Wikis/Cairo-Attractions/wiki/Khan-El-Khalili\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; color: rgb(8, 149, 255); text-decoration: none !important; background-color: transparent;\">&nbsp;</a>Khalili, Cairo&rsquo;s oldest and most alluring bazaar. Later, you will be transferred to the gorgeous Giza train station to catch the sleeper train from Cairo to Aswan. Dinner and breakfast will be served on board. Overnight accommodations inside your compartment.<br />\r\n<strong>Meals:&nbsp;</strong>Breakfast, Lunch, Dinner.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"full_itinerary_box\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 10px; border: 1px solid rgb(235, 235, 235); font-family: Avenir, sans-serif; border-radius: 10px; float: left; width: 700px; position: relative; font-size: 14px; line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(253, 253, 253);\">\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_title\" id=\"itinerary_title_3\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 20px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; float: left; width: 678px; color: rgb(92, 94, 98); cursor: pointer;\">\r\n<h2 style=\"font-style:inherit\">Day 3: Aswan Nile Cruise Tours</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_desc\" id=\"itinerary_desc_3\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 34px 20px; padding: 20px 0px 0px; border-width: 1px 0px 0px; border-top-style: solid; border-top-color: rgb(225, 225, 225); font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 15px;\">\r\n<div style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit;\">Upon your arrival at the Aswan&nbsp;train station, you will be met and assisted by&nbsp;<span style=\"color:#0000FF\"><span style=\"font-family:helvetica,arial,sans-serif\">Signature Tours Egypt</span></span>&nbsp;representative, who will then transfer you to your Nile River cruise ship. Enjoy lunch on board, after which you will be guided to visit the famous High Dam, majestic Philae<a href=\"https://www.memphistours.com/Egypt/Egypt-Wikis/aswan-attractions/wiki/Philae-Temple\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; color: rgb(8, 149, 255); text-decoration: none !important; background-color: transparent;\">&nbsp;</a>Temple&nbsp;of devotion to the two goddesses Isis and Hathor, and the massive Unfinished<a href=\"https://www.memphistours.com/Egypt/Egypt-Wikis/aswan-attractions/wiki/Unfinished-Obelisk\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; color: rgb(8, 149, 255); text-decoration: none !important; background-color: transparent;\">&nbsp;</a>Obelisk, still resting on its side in the stone quarries of ancient Egypt. Then, back to the cruise ship with dinner on board and overnight in Aswan.<br />\r\n<strong>Meals:&nbsp;</strong>Breakfast, Lunch, Dinner.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"full_itinerary_box\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 10px; border: 1px solid rgb(235, 235, 235); font-family: Avenir, sans-serif; border-radius: 10px; float: left; width: 700px; position: relative; font-size: 14px; line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(253, 253, 253);\">\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_title\" id=\"itinerary_title_4\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 20px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; float: left; width: 678px; color: rgb(92, 94, 98); cursor: pointer;\">\r\n<h2 style=\"font-style:inherit\">Day 4: Kom Ombo and Edfu Temples</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_desc\" id=\"itinerary_desc_4\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 34px 20px; padding: 20px 0px 0px; border-width: 1px 0px 0px; border-top-style: solid; border-top-color: rgb(225, 225, 225); font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 15px;\">\r\n<div style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit;\">After breakfast on board, you&rsquo;ll sail to Kom Ombo, where you&rsquo;ll encounter the twin Temple of Kom<a href=\"https://www.memphistours.com/Egypt/Egypt-Wikis/nile-valley/wiki/Kom-Ombo\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; color: rgb(8, 149, 255); text-decoration: none !important; background-color: transparent;\">&nbsp;</a>Ombo, where you&rsquo;ll learn about the crocodile god Sobek and the falcon god Horus, whose monuments decorate each half of the temple. You&rsquo;ll have your lunch back on board the ship and sail on to Edfu, where you&rsquo;ll stop to visit the Temple of<a href=\"https://www.memphistours.com/Egypt/Egypt-Wikis/nile-valley/wiki/Temple-of-Edfu\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; color: rgb(8, 149, 255); text-decoration: none !important; background-color: transparent;\">&nbsp;</a>Edfu, the best-preserved temple of the ancient world. The structure is dedicated to Horus, the falcon god. Reboard the ship for afternoon tea and a leisurely ride to Esna. Dinner and overnight on board.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Meals:</strong>&nbsp;Breakfast, Lunch, Dinner.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"full_itinerary_box\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 10px; border: 1px solid rgb(235, 235, 235); font-family: Avenir, sans-serif; border-radius: 10px; float: left; width: 700px; position: relative; font-size: 14px; line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(253, 253, 253);\">\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_title\" id=\"itinerary_title_5\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 20px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; float: left; width: 678px; color: rgb(92, 94, 98); cursor: pointer;\">\r\n<h2 style=\"font-style:inherit\">Day 5: Luxor Nile Cruise Tours</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_desc\" id=\"itinerary_desc_5\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 34px 20px; padding: 20px 0px 0px; border-width: 1px 0px 0px; border-top-style: solid; border-top-color: rgb(225, 225, 225); font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 15px;\">\r\n<div style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit;\">In the early morning, enjoy a relaxed breakfast on board as you sail to Luxor. You&rsquo;ll then set out to visit the West Bank of Luxor, take an excursion to the Royal Cemetery for 62 Pharaohs, the Valley of the Kings, then to mortuary Temple of Queen<a href=\"https://www.memphistours.com/Egypt/Egypt-Wikis/Egypt-History/wiki/Queen-Hatshepsut\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; color: rgb(8, 149, 255); text-decoration: none !important; background-color: transparent;\">&nbsp;</a>Hatshepsut, which was built by the architects of the New Kingdom during the 15th century BCE at Deir El-Bahari. You&rsquo;ll proceed to the towering Colossi of<a href=\"https://www.memphistours.com/Egypt/Egypt-Wikis/Luxor-Attractions/wiki/Colossi-of-Memnon\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; color: rgb(8, 149, 255); text-decoration: none !important; background-color: transparent;\">&nbsp;</a>Memnon, and then back to the Nile cruise ship and have lunch aboard. As the ship makes its way up the Nile, you&rsquo;ll enjoy afternoon tea. Dinner on board and overnight in Luxor.<br />\r\n<strong>Meals:&nbsp;</strong>Breakfast, Lunch, Dinner.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"full_itinerary_box\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 10px; border: 1px solid rgb(235, 235, 235); font-family: Avenir, sans-serif; border-radius: 10px; float: left; width: 700px; position: relative; font-size: 14px; line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(253, 253, 253);\">\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_title\" id=\"itinerary_title_6\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 20px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; float: left; width: 678px; color: rgb(92, 94, 98); cursor: pointer;\">\r\n<h2 style=\"font-style:inherit\">Day 6: Luxor Nile Cruise - Train to Cairo</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_desc\" id=\"itinerary_desc_6\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 34px 20px; padding: 20px 0px 0px; border-width: 1px 0px 0px; border-top-style: solid; border-top-color: rgb(225, 225, 225); font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 15px;\">\r\n<div style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit;\">Breakfast aboard the cruise before disembarkation, and then you will be accompanied by your tour guide to the ancient Karnak&nbsp;and Luxor<a href=\"https://www.memphistours.com/Egypt/Egypt-Wikis/Luxor-Attractions/wiki/Luxor-Temple\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; color: rgb(8, 149, 255); text-decoration: none !important; background-color: transparent;\">&nbsp;</a>Temples&nbsp;along the east bank of Luxor. Later, you&rsquo;ll head to the Luxor train station to catch the sleeper train back to Cairo. Dinner will be served aboard the train. Overnight in your private compartment.<br />\r\n<strong>Meals:&nbsp;</strong>Breakfast, Dinner.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"full_itinerary_box\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 10px; border: 1px solid rgb(235, 235, 235); font-family: Avenir, sans-serif; border-radius: 10px; float: left; width: 700px; position: relative; font-size: 14px; line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(253, 253, 253);\">\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_title\" id=\"itinerary_title_7\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 20px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; float: left; width: 678px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); cursor: pointer;\">\r\n<h2 style=\"font-style:inherit\">Day 7: Cairo Optional Excursions</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_desc\" id=\"itinerary_desc_7\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 34px 20px; padding: 20px 0px 0px; border-width: 1px 0px 0px; border-top-style: solid; border-top-color: rgb(225, 225, 225); font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 15px;\">\r\n<div style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit;\">Breakfast aboard the sleeper train before arriving at the Giza train station, where you will be met and assisted by&nbsp;<span style=\"color:#0000FF\"><span style=\"font-family:helvetica,arial,sans-serif\">Signature Tours Egypt</span></span> representative who will transfer you to your hotel for some leisure time (you will check into your room as early as possible). There are some optional excursions available in Cairo: you may wish to visit the Step Pyramid of King<a href=\"https://www.memphistours.com/Egypt/Egypt-Wikis/Egypt-Pyramids/wiki/Step-pyramid\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; color: rgb(8, 149, 255); text-decoration: none !important; background-color: transparent;\">&nbsp;</a>Zoser&nbsp;in Sakkara and Memphis. Overnight stay at your hotel in Cairo.<br />\r\n<strong>Meals:</strong>&nbsp;Breakfast.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"full_itinerary_box\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 10px; border: 1px solid rgb(235, 235, 235); font-family: Avenir, sans-serif; border-radius: 10px; float: left; width: 700px; position: relative; font-size: 14px; line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(253, 253, 253);\">\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_title\" id=\"itinerary_title_8\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 20px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; float: left; width: 678px; color: rgb(92, 94, 98); cursor: pointer;\">\r\n<h2 style=\"font-style:inherit\">Day 8: Cairo - Fly Back Home</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_desc\" id=\"itinerary_desc_8\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 34px 20px; padding: 20px 0px 0px; border-width: 1px 0px 0px; border-top-style: solid; border-top-color: rgb(225, 225, 225); font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 15px;\">\r\n<div style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit;\">Enjoy breakfast at your hotel in Cairo, with some free time before your flight. After check out, you&rsquo;ll be escorted to Cairo International Airport for final departure.<br />\r\nMeals: Breakfast &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>Note:&nbsp;</strong><span style=\"font-family:avenir,sans-serif; font-size:14px\">Egyptian trains are designed and maintained according to standards of quality determined by the Egyptian Railway Authority. The sleeper train from Cairo to Aswan takes about 14 hours, and the journey from Luxor to Cairo takes about 11 hours. To reduce time spent traveling, you can upgrade your trip package for about $140&nbsp;per person to travel by domestic flight instead (about 1.5 hours).</span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', '68627283_358393801776301_5140294422667198464_n.jpg', '68574203_330899977793167_1723412767764905984_n.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '800.00', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Meet and greet service by our representatives upon your airport arrival</li>\r\n	<li>Assistance with guest relations during your stay</li>\r\n	<li>All transfers in a private air-conditioned vehicle</li>\r\n	<li>Accommodation for 2 nights in Cairo including bed and breakfast</li>\r\n	<li>Accommodation for 3 nights on a 5-star superior Nile cruise ship, full board</li>\r\n	<li>Accommodation for 2 nights on sleeper train, half board</li>\r\n	<li>Private sightseeing tours in Cairo (listed on itinerary)</li>\r\n	<li>Sightseeing tours on the cruise shared with&nbsp;<span style=\"color:#0000FF\"><span style=\"font-family:helvetica,arial,sans-serif\">Signature Tours Egypt</span></span></li>\r\n	<li>Entrance fees to all sites mentioned on the itinerary</li>\r\n	<li>All meals mentioned on the itinerary</li>\r\n	<li>Local English speaking tour guide.</li>\r\n	<li>Bottled water during outings outside of hotel or cruise ship</li>\r\n	<li>Portage as needed</li>\r\n	<li>30 minutes of local calling (5 minutes international) and a mobile phone loaned for the length of your stay, or an Egyptian SIM card for your unlocked mobile device</li>\r\n	<li>All service charges and taxes</li>\r\n</ul>', '<ul>\r\n	<li>International airfare</li>\r\n	<li>Entry visa to Egypt</li>\r\n	<li>Any optional tours</li>\r\n	<li>Personal spending</li>\r\n	<li>Tipping</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL, 'no', '5', NULL, 'egypt-tours-giza-pyramids-cairo-nile-cruise-luxor-aswan', NULL, NULL, '