(21, 3, 88, '12 Days Pyramids, Nile Cruise & Lake Nasser', 'An unrivalled tour covering Pyramids, the Nile and Lake Nasser Cruise. Discover Cairo and it‚Äôs Pharaonic wonders such as the Pyramids and Sphinx, Museum and Old Coptic and Islamic Cairo to the River Nile by Cruise and the splendors of Lake Nasser and scenic surroundings also by Cruise. Both cruises are of grand design, offering all the luxury one could wish for, and how completely satisfying to know that all the wonderful Ancient sites of Upper Egypt are included both in Luxor with the Valley of the Kings and Temples along the Nile and colourful attractions awaiting you in Aswan including more activities and sites and still the beauty of Lake Nasser and the Great complex of Abu Simbel.', '<div class=\"full_itinerary_box\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 10px; border: 1px solid rgb(235, 235, 235); font-family: Avenir, sans-serif; border-radius: 10px; background-color: rgb(253, 253, 253); float: left; width: 700px; position: relative; font-size: 14px;\">\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_title toggled\" id=\"itinerary_title_1\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 20px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; float: left; width: 678px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); cursor: pointer;\">\r\n<h2 style=\"font-style:inherit\">Day 1: Arrive Cairo &lsquo;Welcome to Egypt</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_desc\" id=\"itinerary_desc_1\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 34px 20px; padding: 20px 0px 0px; border-width: 1px 0px 0px; border-top-style: solid; border-right-style: initial; border-bottom-style: initial; border-left-style: initial; border-top-color: rgb(225, 225, 225); border-right-color: initial; border-bottom-color: initial; border-left-color: initial; border-image: initial; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 15px;\">\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Your Tour Manager will meet and assist you at Cairo International Airport then escort you to your Hotel by exclusive air-conditioned deluxe vehicle. At the Hotel your Tour Manager will assist with a smooth check-in and review your holiday itinerary with you to establish and confirm pick-up times for each tour. Overnight in Cairo. This would be a good time to do an optional excursion to the Sound &amp; Light Show on Giza Plateau, by the magnificent pyramids.<br />\r\n<strong>Welcome Drink</strong></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"full_itinerary_box\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 10px; border: 1px solid rgb(235, 235, 235); font-family: Avenir, sans-serif; border-radius: 10px; background-color: rgb(253, 253, 253); float: left; width: 700px; position: relative; font-size: 14px;\">\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_title toggled\" id=\"itinerary_title_2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 20px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; float: left; width: 678px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); cursor: pointer;\">\r\n<h2 style=\"font-style:inherit\">Day 2: Giza Pyramids and Sakkara</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_desc\" id=\"itinerary_desc_2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 34px 20px; padding: 20px 0px 0px; border-width: 1px 0px 0px; border-top-style: solid; border-right-style: initial; border-bottom-style: initial; border-left-style: initial; border-top-color: rgb(225, 225, 225); border-right-color: initial; border-bottom-color: initial; border-left-color: initial; border-image: initial; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 15px;\">\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">After your breakfast at the Hotel you will visit Sakkara, the first Pyramid ever built in Egypt followed by the Step Pyramid of King Djoser and the Teti Pyramid. Then on to the famous Giza Plateau to visit the only remaining wonder from the original Seven Wonders of the Ancient World - the Great Pyramids of Khufu (called Cheops by the Ancient Greeks). Also on the plateau are the pyramids of Khafre (Chephren) and the smallest Pyramid Menkaure (Mykerinos). The plateau is as famous for the mysterious structure &#39;the Sphinx&#39; as it is for the Pyramids, where you will visit the Valley Temple. Later on you will be transferred back to your hotel and overnight in Cairo.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Note&nbsp;</strong>- There is an additional charge to enter inside any of the Pyramids and also the Solar Boat Museum. Please speak with your Tour Guide if you wish to purchase tickets.<br />\r\n<strong>Meals: Breakfast, Dinner</strong></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"full_itinerary_box\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 10px; border: 1px solid rgb(235, 235, 235); font-family: Avenir, sans-serif; border-radius: 10px; background-color: rgb(253, 253, 253); float: left; width: 700px; position: relative; font-size: 14px;\">\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_title toggled\" id=\"itinerary_title_3\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 20px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; float: left; width: 678px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); cursor: pointer;\">\r\n<h2 style=\"font-style:inherit\">Day 3: Fly Cairo to Luxor - Nile Cruise Tours</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_desc\" id=\"itinerary_desc_3\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 34px 20px; padding: 20px 0px 0px; border-width: 1px 0px 0px; border-top-style: solid; border-right-style: initial; border-bottom-style: initial; border-left-style: initial; border-top-color: rgb(225, 225, 225); border-right-color: initial; border-bottom-color: initial; border-left-color: initial; border-image: initial; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 15px;\">\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">After early breakfast, your Tour Guide will transfer you to Cairo Airport for your flight to Luxor. On arrival you will be met by your Representative to check in to your Nile Cruise in Luxor. After this, you will head off with your Tour Guide to explore Karnak Temple, which is the world&#39;s largest ancient religious site. The hypostyle hall with its colossal granite columns is one of Egypt&rsquo;s infamous landmarks. There will be free time to explore the different parts of the huge complex built during the reigns of various Pharaohs, then moving to Luxor Temple which was built by Amenhotep III and Ramses II for ritual and festivals that was dedicated to the God Amon and you may wish to return in the evening for the highly recommended optional tour, the Sound and Light show which tells the glorious Pharaonic historical story of Luxor and Karnak. Return to your Nile cruise and Overnight in Luxor.<br />\r\n<strong>Meals: Breakfast, Lunch, Dinner</strong></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"full_itinerary_box\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 10px; border: 1px solid rgb(235, 235, 235); font-family: Avenir, sans-serif; border-radius: 10px; background-color: rgb(253, 253, 253); float: left; width: 700px; position: relative; font-size: 14px;\">\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_title toggled\" id=\"itinerary_title_4\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 20px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; float: left; width: 678px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); cursor: pointer;\">\r\n<h2 style=\"font-style:inherit\">Day 4: Luxor Nile Cruise Excursions</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_desc\" id=\"itinerary_desc_4\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 34px 20px; padding: 20px 0px 0px; border-width: 1px 0px 0px; border-top-style: solid; border-right-style: initial; border-bottom-style: initial; border-left-style: initial; border-top-color: rgb(225, 225, 225); border-right-color: initial; border-bottom-color: initial; border-left-color: initial; border-image: initial; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 15px;\">\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Breakfast is served on board in Luxor before being escorted by your Guide to cross to the West Bank of the Nile to the sites of Ancient Thebes, overall one of the most important archaeological sites in the world. Visit the two colossal statues of Amenhotep III (Colossi of Memnon), and the visit the impressive colonnaded and terraced Temple of Hatshepsut at Deir el-Bahri, which was built into a high cliff face and has graphics telling the story of Hatshepsut&rsquo;s expeditions to the mysterious land of Punt. Then you go to The Valley of the Kings to see a selection of the beautifully decorated rock-cut tombs, many of which still display vibrant colour and breathtaking detail of deities and scenes from the Book of the Underworld with a visit to 3 tombs. (The three tombs visited are determined by the Egyptian Government as to preserve them from the large flow of visitors, therefore are rotated throughout the year and cannot be confirmed as to which tombs prior to your visit). The most visited tombs have walkways and electric lighting, and the internal walls are protected by glass. Sailing to Edfu via Esna Lock dinner and overnight stay on board the Nile cruise vessel.<br />\r\n<strong>Please Note:</strong>&nbsp;There is an additional Charge to enter the Tombs of King Tutankhamun and Ramses VI.<br />\r\n<strong>Meals: Breakfast, Lunch, Dinner</strong></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"full_itinerary_box\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 10px; border: 1px solid rgb(235, 235, 235); font-family: Avenir, sans-serif; border-radius: 10px; background-color: rgb(253, 253, 253); float: left; width: 700px; position: relative; font-size: 14px;\">\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_title toggled\" id=\"itinerary_title_5\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 20px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; float: left; width: 678px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); cursor: pointer;\">\r\n<h2 style=\"font-style:inherit\">Day 5: Kom Ombo and Edfu Temples</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_desc\" id=\"itinerary_desc_5\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 34px 20px; padding: 20px 0px 0px; border-width: 1px 0px 0px; border-top-style: solid; border-right-style: initial; border-bottom-style: initial; border-left-style: initial; border-top-color: rgb(225, 225, 225); border-right-color: initial; border-bottom-color: initial; border-left-color: initial; border-image: initial; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 15px;\">\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">After enjoying breakfast onboard your Nile cruise ship in Aswan you sail to see Kom Ombo Temple . Of all the ancient temples in Egypt, this is the only one which is divided into two, to reflect that it is dedicated to two Gods: Sobek, the Crocodile God of fertility; and the falcon-headed Horus, God of the sky. Kom Ombo is also famous for the depictions of surgeon&#39;s instruments, giving us an early record of medicine and surgery in Ancient Egypt.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><br />\r\nIn the afternoon, sailing down the Nile to visit the huge Ptolemaic Temple of Horus at Edfu, which is the most complete and best preserved of the Egyptian Temples, consisting of many columns, halls, chambers and chapels. Two statues of Horus flank the twin towered entrance gate; and inside, one of the interesting inscriptions lists the titles of books (scrolls) held in the library.Back to your Nile cruise for dinner, afternoon tea is served on the sundeck with dinner sailing to Aswan overnight stay.<br />\r\n<strong>Meals: Breakfast, Lunch, Dinner</strong></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"full_itinerary_box\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 10px; border: 1px solid rgb(235, 235, 235); font-family: Avenir, sans-serif; border-radius: 10px; background-color: rgb(253, 253, 253); float: left; width: 700px; position: relative; font-size: 14px;\">\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_title toggled\" id=\"itinerary_title_6\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 20px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; float: left; width: 678px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); cursor: pointer;\">\r\n<h2 style=\"font-style:inherit\">Day 6: Aswan Nile Cruise Tours</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_desc\" id=\"itinerary_desc_6\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 34px 20px; padding: 20px 0px 0px; border-width: 1px 0px 0px; border-top-style: solid; border-right-style: initial; border-bottom-style: initial; border-left-style: initial; border-top-color: rgb(225, 225, 225); border-right-color: initial; border-bottom-color: initial; border-left-color: initial; border-image: initial; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 15px;\">\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">After enjoying breakfast onboard your cruise ship in Aswan you will be met by your Guide to visit the Aswan High Dam which was built in the 1960&rsquo;s to provide the much needed electricity and irrigation for the country. Nubia, the area that was flooded, experienced the biggest and most thorough archaeological excavations that Egypt has ever known. Then moving on to witness the &lsquo;Unfinished Obelisk&rsquo; which still lies in the granite quarries which provided ancient Egypt with building materials.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">It would have been the largest piece of stone ever handled but when a crack was discovered it was abandoned where it was being hewn. Cross by boat to Angilika Island, to see Philae Temple which is one of the Nubian Temples rescued before the High Dam was built. Enjoy Philae&rsquo;s long colonnades, towers and reliefs which include the last surviving hieroglyphic and demotic inscriptions in Egypt. Return to your Nile cruise ship for lunch, afternoon tea, dinner and leisurely free time in Aswan. Overnight stay aboard the cruise.<br />\r\n<strong>Meals: Breakfast, Lunch, Dinner</strong></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"full_itinerary_box\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 10px; border: 1px solid rgb(235, 235, 235); font-family: Avenir, sans-serif; border-radius: 10px; background-color: rgb(253, 253, 253); float: left; width: 700px; position: relative; font-size: 14px;\">\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_title toggled\" id=\"itinerary_title_7\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 20px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; float: left; width: 678px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); cursor: pointer;\">\r\n<h2 style=\"font-style:inherit\">Day 7: Aswan to Abu Simbel group transfer - Lake Nasser Cruise</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_desc\" id=\"itinerary_desc_7\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 34px 20px; padding: 20px 0px 0px; border-width: 1px 0px 0px; border-top-style: solid; border-right-style: initial; border-bottom-style: initial; border-left-style: initial; border-top-color: rgb(225, 225, 225); border-right-color: initial; border-bottom-color: initial; border-left-color: initial; border-image: initial; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 15px;\">\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Disembark after breakfast. Then join our group transfer to to Abu Simbel (approximately 3.5 hours). Upon arrival at Abu Simbel, you will be transferred to embark on your 5 Star Lake Nasser cruise. Check in at Abu Simbel with lunch on board then your fascinating exploration of these enormous twin Temples of Abu Simbel.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><br />\r\n<strong>Note*</strong>&nbsp;Optional flight from Aswan to Abu Simbel as upgrade is available upon request<br />\r\n<strong>Meals: Breakfast, Lunch, Dinner</strong></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"full_itinerary_box\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 10px; border: 1px solid rgb(235, 235, 235); font-family: Avenir, sans-serif; border-radius: 10px; background-color: rgb(253, 253, 253); float: left; width: 700px; position: relative; font-size: 14px;\">\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_title toggled\" id=\"itinerary_title_8\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 20px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; float: left; width: 678px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); cursor: pointer;\">\r\n<h2 style=\"font-style:inherit\">Day 8: Lake Nasser Cruise Tours</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_desc\" id=\"itinerary_desc_8\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 34px 20px; padding: 20px 0px 0px; border-width: 1px 0px 0px; border-top-style: solid; border-right-style: initial; border-bottom-style: initial; border-left-style: initial; border-top-color: rgb(225, 225, 225); border-right-color: initial; border-bottom-color: initial; border-left-color: initial; border-image: initial; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 15px;\">\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Enjoy breakfast while sailing to Kasr Ibrim. View Kasr Ibrim Fortress from the sun deck sailing to Amada where you will visit the Temple of Amada, Ed Deir and the Tomb of Pennut. Return to ship for lunch while sailing to Wadi el Seboua. Dinner and overnight on board the ship.<br />\r\n<strong>Meals: Breakfast, Lunch, Dinner</strong></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"full_itinerary_box\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 10px; border: 1px solid rgb(235, 235, 235); font-family: Avenir, sans-serif; border-radius: 10px; background-color: rgb(253, 253, 253); float: left; width: 700px; position: relative; font-size: 14px;\">\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_title toggled\" id=\"itinerary_title_9\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 20px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; float: left; width: 678px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); cursor: pointer;\">\r\n<h2 style=\"font-style:inherit\">Day 9: Lake Nasser Cruise Tours</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_desc\" id=\"itinerary_desc_9\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 34px 20px; padding: 20px 0px 0px; border-width: 1px 0px 0px; border-top-style: solid; border-right-style: initial; border-bottom-style: initial; border-left-style: initial; border-top-color: rgb(225, 225, 225); border-right-color: initial; border-bottom-color: initial; border-left-color: initial; border-image: initial; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 15px;\">\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">After Breakfast visit Wadi el Seboua, then take a camel ride or walk to el Dakka and Mehraka. Back to the ship to sail to Aswan. Dinner and overnight on board.<br />\r\n<strong>Meals: Breakfast, Lunch, Dinner</strong></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"full_itinerary_box\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 10px; border: 1px solid rgb(235, 235, 235); font-family: Avenir, sans-serif; border-radius: 10px; background-color: rgb(253, 253, 253); float: left; width: 700px; position: relative; font-size: 14px;\">\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_title toggled\" id=\"itinerary_title_10\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 20px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; float: left; width: 678px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); cursor: pointer;\">\r\n<h2 style=\"font-style:inherit\">Day 10: Lake Nasser Cruise - Fly to Cairo</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_desc\" id=\"itinerary_desc_10\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 34px 20px; padding: 20px 0px 0px; border-width: 1px 0px 0px; border-top-style: solid; border-right-style: initial; border-bottom-style: initial; border-left-style: initial; border-top-color: rgb(225, 225, 225); border-right-color: initial; border-bottom-color: initial; border-left-color: initial; border-image: initial; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 15px;\">\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">After breakfast, disembark the lake Cruise to visit Kalabsha temple, dedicated to the Nubian God Mandulis then continue to Beit el Wali to visit the beautiful Kiosk of Kertassi to explore the Nubian style Temple dedicated to the Goddess Hathor. Finally you will be transferred from your Cruise Boat by an air conditioned vehicle to Aswan Airport for your flight back to Cairo. Overnight in the Hotel at Cairo.<br />\r\n<strong>Meals: Breakfast</strong></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"full_itinerary_box\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 10px; border: 1px solid rgb(235, 235, 235); font-family: Avenir, sans-serif; border-radius: 10px; background-color: rgb(253, 253, 253); float: left; width: 700px; position: relative; font-size: 14px;\">\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_title toggled\" id=\"itinerary_title_11\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 20px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; float: left; width: 678px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); cursor: pointer;\">\r\n<h2 style=\"font-style:inherit\">Day 11: Cairo Sightseeing Tours</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_desc\" id=\"itinerary_desc_11\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 34px 20px; padding: 20px 0px 0px; border-width: 1px 0px 0px; border-top-style: solid; border-right-style: initial; border-bottom-style: initial; border-left-style: initial; border-top-color: rgb(225, 225, 225); border-right-color: initial; border-bottom-color: initial; border-left-color: initial; border-image: initial; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 15px;\">\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Last day in Cairo, you will take breakfast at the Hotel, then be escorted by your Tour Guide to visit the world-renowned Egyptian Museum in Cairo that was built in neo-classical style and designed by the French architect Marcel Dourgnon. The museum&#39;s vast collection of over 120,000 artifacts ranges from pre-dynastic era, through the Pharaonic era to the Greco-Roman period of Egypt. Amongst the most famous items which you may see are the funerary treasures of the child King Tutankhamun, the colossal statues of the heretic king, Akhenaten, and the only surviving image of Khufu, creator of Egypt&#39;s Great Pyramid. Visiting the museum is a great introduction to learning about the ancient Egyptian civilization, including their famous art of mummification.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><br />\r\nNext will be an unusual opportunity to explore the Christian heritage in Coptic Cairo including some of the early religious monuments of the city such as the Hanging Church (or Suspended Church), this Basilica Church was named for its location on top of the south gate of the Fortress of Babylon. This Church became the centre of the Christian Church of Egypt. Afterwards, you will have a wonderful afternoon shopping at the famous old market in Cairo known as Khan El Khalili Bazaar. Overnight stay in Cairo with free leisure time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><br />\r\n<strong>Please Note*</strong>&nbsp;There is an additional charge to enter the Mummies Room at the Museum. Please speak with your Tour Guide should you wish to purchase a ticket to enter one of these sites.<br />\r\n<strong>Meals: Breakfast, Lunch</strong></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"full_itinerary_box\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 10px; border: 1px solid rgb(235, 235, 235); font-family: Avenir, sans-serif; border-radius: 10px; background-color: rgb(253, 253, 253); float: left; width: 700px; position: relative; font-size: 14px;\">\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_title toggled\" id=\"itinerary_title_12\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 20px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; float: left; width: 678px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); cursor: pointer;\">\r\n<h2 style=\"font-style:inherit\">Day 12: Cairo - Fly Back Home</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_desc\" id=\"itinerary_desc_12\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 34px 20px; padding: 20px 0px 0px; border-width: 1px 0px 0px; border-top-style: solid; border-right-style: initial; border-bottom-style: initial; border-left-style: initial; border-top-color: rgb(225, 225, 225); border-right-color: initial; border-bottom-color: initial; border-left-color: initial; border-image: initial; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 15px;\">\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">After breakfast at the Hotel in Cairo, you will be transferred to Cairo International Airport for your flight home<br />\r\n<strong>Meals: Breakfast</strong></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', '68627283_358393801776301_5140294422667198464_n.jpg', '69206160_755385951561635_3115813561373294592_n.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2340.00', '<div class=\"scroll_pane_new\" id=\"overview\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-family: Avenir, sans-serif; width: 700px; float: left; font-size: 14px;\">\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Met and assisted at Cairo airport upon arrival and departure by our Representative.</li>\r\n	<li>Expert assistance and guidance during your stay by our Personnel, including all tours mentioned.</li>\r\n	<li>All airport transfers by private deluxe A/C vehicle.</li>\r\n	<li>Accommodation for 4 nights at a Cairo Hotel on buffet breakfast basis</li>\r\n	<li>Accommodation for 4 nights on board Nile Cruise on full board basis.</li>\r\n	<li>Accommodation for 3 nights on board Lake Nasser cruise on full board basis.</li>\r\n	<li>Domestic flights (Cairo to Luxor &mdash; Aswan to Cairo) are included.\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>All&nbsp;excursions as mentioned will be Private</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>Tour to Karnak &nbsp;and Luxor Temples</li>\r\n	<li>Tour to Valley of the Kings, Hatshepsut Temple and Colossi of Memnon.</li>\r\n	<li>Tour to Edfu and Kom Ombo Temples</li>\r\n	<li>Tour to the High Dam, Unfinished Obelisk and Temple of Philae.</li>\r\n	<li>Tour to the Temples of Abu Simbel</li>\r\n	<li>Tour to the temples of Amada and Derr</li>\r\n	<li>Tour to Tomb of Penout</li>\r\n	<li>Tour to Wadi El Seboua and Temples of Dakka &amp; Meharakka</li>\r\n	<li>Tour to the Kalabsha Temple, Beit El Wali, Kiosk of Kertassi</li>\r\n	<li>Lunch meals during tours</li>\r\n	<li>Professional English-speaking Tour Guide.</li>\r\n	<li>Admission fees to the sights throughout the tours.</li>\r\n	<li>Free loan of mobile phone charged against 30 min local calls / 3 min. international calls.</li>\r\n	<li>Applicable taxes for all hotels and Nile cruises included in the price.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', '<ul>\r\n	<li>International airfare.</li>\r\n	<li>Entry Visa to Egypt.</li>\r\n	<li>Personal spendings.</li>\r\n	<li>Optional excursions.</li>\r\n	<li>Tipping</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL, 'no', '5', NULL, 'egypt-tours-giza-pyramids-cairo-nile-cruise-luxor-aswan-egyptian-museum-lake-nasser-packages', NULL, NULL, '2019-08-27 15:24:01', '2019-09-02 13:54:42'),
(22, 3, 88, '3 Days Cairo Tour Package', '2 Nights in Cairo', '<h3>Day 1: Arrival &ndash; Egyptian Museum &amp; Old Cairo</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Arrival to Cairo airport, our representative will be waiting you with sign of <span style=\"color:#0000FF\"><span style=\"font-family:helvetica,arial,sans-serif\">Signature Tours Egypt</span></span>, then you will be transferred by an A/C car to enjoy a visit to the Egyptian Museum, which features artifacts from the Pharaonic period.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The museum displays a rare collection of 5000 years of art which is considered the largest most precious collection of Egyptian art in the world. Over 250,000 overwhelming artifacts are presented, including an exhibit dedicated to Tutankhamen collection of treasure, gold and jewelry which was enclosed in his tomb for over 3,500 years before it was discovered in the 1920s when his tomb was excavated.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Then proceed to visit Mohamed Ali Alabaster Mosque and Citadel of Salah El Din. Head to Old Cairo to visit the Hanging Church, Abu Sirga Church and Synagogue. Back to your hotel.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Note:</strong>&nbsp;if will not be able to make the tour on that day due to a late arrival time, then you can make on the last day before your departure flight.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(Optional) Evening trip to enjoy you dinner on board a Nile cruise for 2 hours including watching Egyptian folk shows.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Overnight in Cairo.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Day 2:&nbsp;Giza Pyramids, Sakkara &amp; Memphis</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Breakfast. Our guide will pick you up from your hotel, to enjoy an excursion to The Pyramids of Cheops, Chephren and Mykerinus.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Then proceed to visit the Great Sphinx, the head of a pharaoh with a lion&rsquo;s body, which dates back to the time of Chephren; the tour also includes a visit to the Valley Temple, which belongs to the Pyramids of Chephren.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Move to visit the Step Pyramid of Zoser, the world&rsquo;s oldest major stone structure. It was built in the 3rd Dynasty (around 2630 BC) for King Djoser.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After that transfer to Memphis which was founded by King Menes, and was the capital of Old Egypt during the Old Kingdom, it was considered to be a center of rule and culture for over3000 years the first capital of Egypt, and see the Statue of Ramses II.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(Optional) Evening trip to attend the Sound &amp; Light show in the Pyramids area.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Overnight in Cairo.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Day 3: Departure</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Breakfast at the hotel our representative will transfer you to the airport and assist you at the airport through final departure formalities.</p>', '69538110_412007916333789_7414362456371232768_n.jpg', '69052722_378909799460889_7162266112527171584_n.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '240.00', '<p><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">2 Nights hotel accommodation in Cairo on bed and breakfast basis.</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">1 day tour in Cairo visiting Great pyramids, Sphinx, Memphis &amp; Sakkra</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">1 day tour in Cairo visiting the Egyptian Museum &amp; Old Cairo</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">All Transfers in Cairo.</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">All your tours and excursions are by an A/C vehicle.</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Expert tour guide.</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">All your visits include entrance fees.</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Our prices include all taxes and services</span></p>', '<p><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">International Airfare.</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Egypt entry visa; We can provide you with your visa upon arrival at your request.</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Drinks and any personal expenses.</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Tipping Kitty</span></p>', NULL, 'no', '5', NULL, '3-days-cairo-tour-package-giza-pyramids-egyptian-museum-citadel-memphis-saqqara-tours', NULL, NULL, '2019-08-28 10:32:42', '2019-09-02 14:01:44'),
(23, 3, 88, '13 Days Cairo, Alexandria, Fayoum & Nile Cruise by Flight', '7 Nights in Cairo 1 Night in Alexandria 4 Nights on Cruise board (Luxor & Aswan).', '<h3>Day 1: Cairo</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Arrival to Cairo airport, Upon you arrival you will find our representative waiting you with the sign of Panorama Egypt Tours, then you will be transferred by A/C car to your hotel. Overnight in Cairo.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Day 2:&nbsp;Egyptian Museum &amp; Giza Pyramids</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Breakfast. Start your tour visiting the Egyptian Museum of antiquities. On display is rare collection of 5000 years of art the largest most precious collection of Egyptian art in the world.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Including an exhibit dedicated to the Tutankhamen collection of treasures, gold, and jewelry. Visit the Great Pyramids &ndash; Cheops, Chephren &amp; Mykerions &amp; Sphinx.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(Optional) Evening trip to attend the Sound &amp; Light show in the Pyramids area.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Overnight in Cairo.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Day 3: Cairo/ Nile Cruise</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Breakfast. Transfer to the domestic airport. Departure by the plane to Luxor. Arrival and transfer to visit The Temple of Karnak &amp; the Temple of Luxor. Excursion to the Luxor Temple to see its courtyard and the granite statues of Ramses the Great. Proceed to Karnak.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Transfer to the Nile Cruise. Boarding before Lunch. Lunch on board. Overnight in Luxor.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Day 4: Nile cruise</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Breakfast.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(Optional) Hot Balloon: Should you want to make your stay in Luxor an unforgettable. Drifting peacefully over the Valley of King, Valley of the Queens and the Mountain on the Nobles.<br />\r\nThe flight is approximately 30:45 minutes depend on the weather</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Visit The West Bank &ndash; the Valley of the Kings, Colossi of Memnon and The Temple of Queen Hatshepsut at El Deir El Bahari. Overnight in Cruise.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Day 5: Nile Cruise</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Breakfast on board. Visit the Temple of Horus in Edfu. Sail to Kom Ombo. Lunch on board. Visit the Temple shared by the two Gods Sobek &amp; Haroeris in Kom Ombo. Afternoon Tea. Overnight in Kom Ombo.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Day 6: Nile Cruise</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Breakfast on board. Sail to Aswan. Visit the High Dam, the Granite Quarries &amp; the Temple of Philae Lunch on board. Overnight in Aswan.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Day 7: Aswan / Cairo</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Breakfast on board. Disembarkation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(Optional) Departure to visit the Temple of Abu Simbel, The colossal Temple of Abu Simbel built by Ramses II (XIXth. Dynasty) and lately saved from inundation of the Nile waters in among the glories of ancient Egyptian monuments. The temples were built out of a sandstone rock cliff, and representation of the deities to which each was dedicated is carved on its huge fa&ccedil;ade. Nearby, also saved, lies the small Temple of the King&rsquo;s wife Nefertari, dedicated to the goddess Hathor. Back to Aswan.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Transfer to Aswan airport and departure by plane to Cairo. Arrival and transfer to the hotel. Overnight in Cairo.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Day 8: Alexandria</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Breakfast. Our tour guide will pick you up from your hotel to start your tour to Alexandria. Travel to Alexandria.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Start the tour with the library of Alexandria; the biggest library in the world &ndash; now with 8 million books. Visit it&rsquo;s open court.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Note: Alexandria Library is closed on Fridays and on every public holiday. To enter the reading area you will need to purchase an extra ticket.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Then visit the Site of the Lighthouse; one of the Seven Wonders of the Ancient World on which now stands the castle of Qaitbey. Visit the royal gardens of King Farouk (the last king in the history of Egypt) and see the royal palaces of Haramlek and Salamlek as well as the royal beaches of the queens. Continue your tour by visiting the prettiest and biggest mosque in the city: the Abbo Elabbas Mosque, as well as the memorial of the Unknown Soldier of Alexandria and the statue of Alexander the Great.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You can then stop for lunch (Optional) before visiting the church of St. Mark &ndash; the oldest church in Africa before driving along the Cornish (30 km) to see the whole city of Alexandria from the sea side which includes the old harbor of Alexandria where we found 7000 monuments underwater. Stop over the famous bridge of Stanley &ndash; the modern landmark of modern Alexandria, before visiting the old downtown of Alexandria and walking through the old city-center of Alexandria: built by Alexander the great. Travel in comfort back to your hotel.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Alexandria has so much to see, feel, eat and buy so if you have time and want to add more to your itinerary &ndash; just let us know what you are interested in and we will arrange it for you at the cost price &ndash; no profit to us.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Overnight in Alexandria.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Day 9:&nbsp;Old Islamic &amp; Coptic Cairo</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Breakfast. Transfer to Cairo by an A/C car. Arrival and transfer to visit Salah El Din Citadel which was constructed by Salah El Din on the Moqattam hills in 1183 AD to defend Cairo from the armies of Crusaders.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After that visit Mohamed Ali Alabaster Mosque which was designed by the architect Yousif Boushnaq, a Turkish man who came specially from Istanbul and built this great mosque for Mohamed Ali, the ruler of Egypt (1805-1849) who ruled Over 45 years.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Then proceed to Visit Old Cairo where you will enjoy, the Hanging Church, Ben Ezra Synagogue, Church of St. Barbara, Church of Abu Serga. Move to the hotel &amp; overnight in Cairo.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Day 10: Fayoum Oasis &amp; Wadi Al-Rian Day Trip</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Breakfast. Transfer to Fayoum by an A/C car. Arrival and&nbsp;start your Fayoum Oasis &amp; Wadi Al Rian Day Tour from Cairo, you will visit Quaran Lake which consider one of the oldest lake in the world, after that you will move to continue your tour to Fayoum Oasis.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After that you will move to Wadi Al Rian.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Move to the hotel &amp; overnight in Cairo.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Day 11: Cairo free day</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Breakfast. Free day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Overnight in Cairo.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Day 12: Sakkara, Memphis &amp; Dahshur</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Breakfast. Visit the Step Pyramids of Zoser, the world&rsquo;s oldest major stone structure. It was built in the 3rd Dynasty (around 2630 BC) for King Djoser.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After that transfer to Memphis which was founded by King Menes, and was the capital of Old Egypt during the Old Kingdom, it was considered to be a center of rule and culture for over 3000 years the first capital of Egypt, and see the Statue of Ramses II. On your way to the south you will visit the Red Pyramid and Bent Pyramid at Dahshur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Overnight in Cairo.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Day 13: Cairo- Departure</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Breakfast at the hotel our representative will transfer you to the airport and assist you at the airport through final departure formalities.</p>', '68627283_358393801776301_5140294422667198464_n.jpg', '68474623_1572807952849965_2846593474977857536_n.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1650.00', '<p><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">7 Nights hotel accommodation in Cairo on bed and breakfast basis.</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">1 Night hotel accommodation in Alexandria on bed and breakfast basis.</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">4 Nights on Cruise board (Luxor &amp; Aswan) full board (Sightseeing are included).</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">1 Day tour in Cairo visiting the Egyptian Museum, Pyramids, Sphinx.</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">1 Day tour in Cairo visiting the Citadel &amp; Old Cairo.</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">1 Day tour in Alexandria.</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">1 Day tour in Fayoum.</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">1 Day tour in Cairo visiting Sakkara, Memphis &amp; Dahshur.</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">All transfers in Cairo, Luxor, and Aswan.</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">All your tours and excursions are by an A/C vehicle.</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Expert tour guide.</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">All your visits include entrance fees.</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Our prices include all taxes and services.</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Domestic airfare: Cairo/ Luxor &amp; Aswan / Cairo</span></p>', '<p><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Visa Entry for Egypt.(We can provide you with your visa upon arrival at your request)</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">International Flights.</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Personal items.</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Tipping.</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Any other items not mentioned.</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Any Optional tours.</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Drinks during meals.</span></p>', NULL, 'no', '5', NULL, 'days-cairo-alexandria-fayoum-nile-cruise-by-flight-giza-pyramids-egyptian-museum-coptic-cairo-islamic-cairo-memphis-packages', NULL, '2019-08-28 12:49:10', '2019-08-28 12:37:39', '2019-08-28 12:49:10'),
(24, 3, 86, 'Fayoum Oasis & Wadi Al Rian Day Tour from Cairo', 'Quaran Lake Fayoum Oasis Wadi Al Rian', '<p>Your&nbsp;<span style=\"color:#0000FF\"><span style=\"font-family:helvetica,arial,sans-serif\">Signature</span></span>&nbsp;tour guide will be waiting you. They&nbsp;will be holding&nbsp; a sign of <span style=\"color:#0000FF\"><span style=\"font-family:helvetica,arial,sans-serif\">Signature Tours Egypt</span></span>, You do not need to look for them &ndash; they will be waiting for you and will find you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>From the moment your tour starts, your guide will give you full attention. Once in the car, your guide will talk to you about all the things on the way as well as other aspects of your tour that will interest you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Start your Fayoum Oasis &amp; Wadi Al Rian Day Tour from Cairo, you will visit Quaran Lake which consider one of the oldest lake in the world, after that you will move to continue your tour to Fayoum Oasis.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After that you will move to Wadi Al Rian.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Travel in comfort back to your hotel in Cairo, Fayoum&nbsp;has so much to see, feel, eat and buy so if you have time and want to add more to your itinerary &ndash; just let us know what you are interested in and we will arrange it for you.</p>', '625446_500805576623706_850836391_n.jpg', '230695_147660901970469_2983225_n.jpg', 'Fayoum Oasis & Wadi Al Rian', NULL, NULL, NULL, '89.00', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Air conditioned van with modern model</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Expert tour guide</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">All the entrance fees to all the mentioned sites in our program</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">All 