(33, 3, 89, 'Discovering King Tut‚Äôs Tomb Tour', 'On this 4-5 hours tour visit Valley of the Kings, King Tut‚Äôs tomb which you will visit from inside and hear about all the lesser-known facts about Tutankhamun, Temple of Queen Hatshepsut & Colossi of Memnon', '<p>Your&nbsp;<span style=\"color:#0000FF\"><span style=\"font-family:helvetica,arial,sans-serif\">Signature</span></span>&nbsp;Tours guide will be waiting you. They will be holding a sign of <span style=\"color:#0000FF\"><span style=\"font-family:helvetica,arial,sans-serif\">Signature Tours Egypt,</span></span>&nbsp;You do not need to look for them &ndash; they will be waiting for you and will find you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>From the moment your tour starts, your guide will give you full attention. Once in the car, your guide will talk to you about all the things on the way as well as other aspects of your tour that will interest you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Start your tour visiting Valley of the Kings, the magnificence of the grandeur of architecture which was used for burial, there are many kings buried in this valley. You will visit 3 tombs including Tomb of King Tutankhamun.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Tutankhamun ruled Egypt for approximately 10 years from around 1336-1327 BCE. In November 1922, Howard Carter and Lord Carnarvon discovered Tutankhamun&rsquo;s near-intact tomb in the Valley of the Kings. The king&rsquo;s mummified body was found surrounded by precious grave goods, in his golden coffin, after his burial chamber was officially opened on 17 February 1923 in the presence of Egyptologists and government officials</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Today, Tutankhamun is ancient Egypt&rsquo;s most famous pharaoh. But how much do you really know about the boy king? Here during this tour, I will tell you the lesser-known facts about Tutankhamun&hellip;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Move on to enjoy the Temple of Queen Hatshepsut, which was built by Queen Hatshepsut, daughter of Thutmosis I, who ruled Egypt about 20 years during the 18th Dynasty (approximately from 1490 to 1469 B.C), the only pharaonic woman who reigned ancient Egypt.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\">You will stop by the Colossi of Memnon for about 15 minutes, and also at the mortuary temple of Amenhotep III.</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\">Travel in comfort back to your hotel, Luxor has so much to see, feel, eat and buy so if you have time and want to add more to your itinerary &ndash; just let us know what you are interested in and we will arrange it for you.</div>', '65305567_10156720219879541_3419773022590992384_n.jpg', '59967367_10156604560394541_6097193216157679616_n.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '50.00', '<p><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Pick up services from your hotel in Luxor and return</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">All transfers by air-conditioned vehicle</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Expert tour guide</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Entrance fees to all the mentioned sites</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">All service charges &amp; taxes</span></p>', '<p><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Any extras not mentioned in the program</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Tipping</span></p>', NULL, 'no', '5', NULL, 'discovering-king-tuts-tomb-tour-queen-hatshepsut-amenhotep-iii-colossi-of-memnon-pharaoh', NULL, NULL, '2019-08-28 15:59:31', '2019-09-02 15:05:34'),
(34, 3, 90, 'Trip to Kom Ombo and Edfu from Aswan', 'Trip to Kom Ombo and Edfu from Aswan', '<p style=\"direction: ltr; \">Your Panorama Egypt Tours guide will be waiting you. They&nbsp;will be holding&nbsp; a sign of Panorama Egypt Tours, You do not need to look for them &ndash; they will be waiting for you and will find you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">From the moment your tour starts, your guide will give you full attention. Once in the car, your guide will talk to you about all the things on the way as well as other aspects of your tour that will interest you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">Enjoy a day tour to the Temple of Kom Ombo standing on high grounds overlooking the Nile.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">It differs from other temples because of its double entrance, each one is dedicated to divinity: &ldquo;Haroeris&rdquo; with his falcon head and &rdquo; Sobek &rdquo; with his crocodile head.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">The Temple of Kom Ombo was built on the honor of two deities the crocodile-headed Sobek, god of fertility and creator of the world, and Haroeris or the ancient falcon-headed Horus.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">(Optional) Lunch will be served at a local restaurant. Then transferred to Edfu by road to visit the majestic temple dedicated to Horus which is considered by most to be the best preserved cult temple in Egypt.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr; \">According to the Egyptian myths, it was the place where the falcon-headed god Horus revenged the murder of his father Osiris by killing Seth.</p>', '3345_75000229861_3933596_n.jpg', '21616066_1536354646457172_8854766790254930236_n.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '85.00', '<p style=\"direction: ltr; \"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Pick up service from your hotel in Aswan and return</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Professional tour guide</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Entrance fees to the mentioned historical places</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">All transfers by a modern air-conditioned vehicle</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">All service charges and taxes</span></p>', '<p style=\"direction: ltr; \"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Any extras not mentioned in the program</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Tipping</span></p>', NULL, 'no', '5', NULL, 'kom-ombo-and-edfu-haroeris-sobek-aswan', NULL, '2019-08-28 16:26:47', '2019-08-28 16:22:51', '2019-08-28 16:26:47'),
(35, 3, 90, 'Trip to Kom Ombo and Edfu from Aswan', 'Trip to Kom Ombo and Edfu from Aswan', '<p>Your&nbsp;<span style=\"color:#0000FF\"><span style=\"font-family:helvetica,arial,sans-serif\">Signature</span></span>&nbsp;Tour guide will be waiting you. They&nbsp;will be holding&nbsp; a sign of <span style=\"color:#0000FF\"><span style=\"font-family:helvetica,arial,sans-serif\">Signature Tours Egypt</span></span>, You do not need to look for them &ndash; they will be waiting for you and will find you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>From the moment your tour starts, your guide will give you full attention. Once in the car, your guide will talk to you about all the things on the way as well as other aspects of your tour that will interest you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Enjoy a day tour to the Temple of Kom Ombo standing on high grounds overlooking the Nile.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It differs from other temples because of its double entrance, each one is dedicated to divinity: &ldquo;Haroeris&rdquo; with his falcon head and &rdquo; Sobek &rdquo; with his crocodile head.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Temple of Kom Ombo was built on the honor of two deities the crocodile-headed Sobek, god of fertility and creator of the world, and Haroeris or the ancient falcon-headed Horus.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(Optional) Lunch will be served at a local restaurant. Then transferred to Edfu by road to visit the majestic temple dedicated to Horus which is considered by most to be the best preserved cult temple in Egypt.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>According to the Egyptian myths, it was the place where the falcon-headed god Horus revenged the murder of his father Osiris by killing Seth.</p>', '3345_75000229861_3933596_n.jpg', '21616066_1536354646457172_8854766790254930236_n.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '85.00', '<p><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Pick up service from your hotel in Aswan and return</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Professional tour guide</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Entrance fees to the mentioned historical places</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">All transfers by a modern air-conditioned vehicle</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">All service charges and taxes</span></p>', '<p><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Any extras not mentioned in the program</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Tipping</span></p>', NULL, 'no', '5', NULL, 'kom-ombo-and-edfu-haroeris-sobek-aswan', NULL, NULL, '2019-08-28 16:22:58', '2019-09-02 15:18:08'),
(36, 3, 91, '10 days Luxury Cairo & Nile Cruise', 'Enjoy a luxurious tour of the Nile Valley. Start in Cairo to see the pyramids before traveling south for 4 days on a Nile cruise, relaxing and taking in the sights of ancient Egypt. Return to Cairo for 3 more days to see the Egyptian Museum, Old Cairo, Saladin‚Äôs Citadel and more.', '<div class=\"full_itinerary_box\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 10px; border: 1px solid rgb(235, 235, 235); font-family: Avenir, sans-serif; border-radius: 10px; background-color: rgb(253, 253, 253); float: left; width: 700px; position: relative; font-size: 14px;\">\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_title toggled\" id=\"itinerary_title_1\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 20px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; float: left; width: 678px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); cursor: pointer;\">\r\n<h2 style=\"font-style:inherit\">Day&nbsp;1: Arrival Cairo - Welcome to Egypt</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_desc\" id=\"itinerary_desc_1\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 34px 20px; padding: 20px 0px 0px; border-width: 1px 0px 0px; border-top-style: solid; border-right-style: initial; border-bottom-style: initial; border-left-style: initial; border-top-color: rgb(225, 225, 225); border-right-color: initial; border-bottom-color: initial; border-left-color: initial; border-image: initial; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 15px;\">\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Welcome to Cairo, Egypt&nbsp;(Around The Clock)<br />\r\nYour tour manager will meet &amp; assist you at Cairo International Airport (Arrival Procedures) and then he will escort you to the hotel by exclusive air-conditioned deluxe vehicle. At hotel the tour manager will assist with a smooth check-in and review your holiday itinerary with you to establish and confirm pick-up times for each tour. Overnight in Cairo.<br />\r\n<em><strong>Welcome Drink</strong></em></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"full_itinerary_box\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 10px; border: 1px solid rgb(235, 235, 235); font-family: Avenir, sans-serif; border-radius: 10px; background-color: rgb(253, 253, 253); float: left; width: 700px; position: relative; font-size: 14px;\">\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_title toggled\" id=\"itinerary_title_2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 20px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; float: left; width: 678px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); cursor: pointer;\">\r\n<h2 style=\"font-style:inherit\">Day 2: Pyramids and Sakkara Tour</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_desc\" id=\"itinerary_desc_2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 34px 20px; padding: 20px 0px 0px; border-width: 1px 0px 0px; border-top-style: solid; border-right-style: initial; border-bottom-style: initial; border-left-style: initial; border-top-color: rgb(225, 225, 225); border-right-color: initial; border-bottom-color: initial; border-left-color: initial; border-image: initial; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 15px;\">\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Breakfast then move to start your blissful day kicking off with the Step Pyramid&nbsp;at Sakkara&nbsp;which was designed by the architect, Imhotep for his master King Zoser. Lunch at a good quality local restaurant. After that, move to visit the enchanting pyramids of Cheops, Chefren&nbsp;and Mykerinus&nbsp;at Giza. Then proceed to visit the Great Sphinx, the head of a pharaoh with a lion&#39;s body, dates back to the time of Chephren. The tour also includes a visit to the Valley Temple&nbsp;which belongs to the Pyramid of Chephren. Overnight in Cairo.<br />\r\n<strong>Meals: Breakfast, Lunch</strong></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"full_itinerary_box\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 10px; border: 1px solid rgb(235, 235, 235); font-family: Avenir, sans-serif; border-radius: 10px; background-color: rgb(253, 253, 253); float: left; width: 700px; position: relative; font-size: 14px;\">\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_title toggled\" id=\"itinerary_title_3\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 20px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; float: left; width: 678px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); cursor: pointer;\">\r\n<h2 style=\"font-style:inherit\">Day 3: Fly Cairo to Luxor - Nile Cruise Tours</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_desc\" id=\"itinerary_desc_3\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 34px 20px; padding: 20px 0px 0px; border-width: 1px 0px 0px; border-top-style: solid; border-right-style: initial; border-bottom-style: initial; border-left-style: initial; border-top-color: rgb(225, 225, 225); border-right-color: initial; border-bottom-color: initial; border-left-color: initial; border-image: initial; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 15px;\">\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Transfer to Cairo Airport for flight to Luxor&nbsp;where you will be met and transferred to embark your 05 star luxury Nile Cruise. In the afternoon you will be accompanied for a wonderful tour to the East Bank of the River<a href=\"https://www.memphistours.com/Egypt/Egypt-Wikis/Egypt-Destinations/wiki/The-Nile-Valley\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(8, 149, 255); text-decoration-line: none !important;\" target=\"_blank\">&nbsp;</a>Nile&nbsp;in Luxor. Here you will see the captivating Karnak&nbsp;and Luxor<a href=\"https://www.memphistours.com/Egypt/Egypt-Wikis/Luxor-Attractions/wiki/Luxor-Temple\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(8, 149, 255); text-decoration-line: none !important;\" title=\"Luxor Temple\">&nbsp;</a>Temples&nbsp;that reflect the bewitching Pharaonic history. Return to the ship for afternoon tea and dinner. Overnight in Luxor.<br />\r\n<em><strong>Meals: Breakfast, Lunch, Dinner</strong></em></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"full_itinerary_box\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 10px; border: 1px solid rgb(235, 235, 235); font-family: Avenir, sans-serif; border-radius: 10px; background-color: rgb(253, 253, 253); float: left; width: 700px; position: relative; font-size: 14px;\">\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_title toggled\" id=\"itinerary_title_4\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 20px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; float: left; width: 678px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); cursor: pointer;\">\r\n<h2 style=\"font-style:inherit\">Day 4: Luxor Nile Cruise Sightseeing</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_desc\" id=\"itinerary_desc_4\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 34px 20px; padding: 20px 0px 0px; border-width: 1px 0px 0px; border-top-style: solid; border-right-style: initial; border-bottom-style: initial; border-left-style: initial; border-top-color: rgb(225, 225, 225); border-right-color: initial; border-bottom-color: initial; border-left-color: initial; border-image: initial; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 15px;\">\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">After breakfast transfer to the West Bank of the Nile in Luxor and visit the Valley of the<a href=\"https://www.memphistours.com/Egypt/Egypt-Wikis/Luxor-Attractions/wiki/Valley-of-the-Kings\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(8, 149, 255); text-decoration-line: none !important;\" title=\"Valley of the Kings\">&nbsp;</a>Kings, Hatshepsut<a href=\"https://www.memphistours.com/Egypt/Egypt-Wikis/Luxor-Attractions/wiki/Temple-of-Hatshepsut\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(8, 149, 255); text-decoration-line: none !important;\" title=\"Temple of Hatshepsut\">&nbsp;</a>Temple&nbsp;at El Deir EL Bahari, and the Colossi of<a href=\"https://www.memphistours.com/Egypt/Egypt-Wikis/Luxor-Attractions/wiki/Colossi-of-Memnon\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(8, 149, 255); text-decoration-line: none !important;\">&nbsp;</a>Memnon. Return to the ship for lunch &amp; afternoon tea while sailing to Edfu via the Esna Lock. Dinner on board. Overnight in Edfu<a href=\"https://www.memphistours.com/Egypt/Egypt-Wikis/nile-valley/wiki/Temple-of-Edfu\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(8, 149, 255); text-decoration-line: none !important;\">.</a><br />\r\n<em><strong>Meals: Breakfast, Lunch, Dinner</strong></em></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"full_itinerary_box\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 10px; border: 1px solid rgb(235, 235, 235); font-family: Avenir, sans-serif; border-radius: 10px; background-color: rgb(253, 253, 253); float: left; width: 700px; position: relative; font-size: 14px;\">\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_title toggled\" id=\"itinerary_title_5\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 20px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; float: left; width: 678px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); cursor: pointer;\">\r\n<h2 style=\"font-style:inherit\">Day 5: Edfu &amp; Kom Ombo Temples</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_desc\" id=\"itinerary_desc_5\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 34px 20px; padding: 20px 0px 0px; border-width: 1px 0px 0px; border-top-style: solid; border-right-style: initial; border-bottom-style: initial; border-left-style: initial; border-top-color: rgb(225, 225, 225); border-right-color: initial; border-bottom-color: initial; border-left-color: initial; border-image: initial; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 15px;\">\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Enjoy breakfast on board before visiting Horus Temple at Edfu.&nbsp;Return to the ship for lunch and sail to Kom Ombo. Upon arrival, visit the temple shared by the two gods Sobek and Haroeris. Return to the ship and continue sailing to Aswan. Dinner on board. Overnight in Aswan.<br />\r\n<em><strong>Meals: Breakfast, Lunch, Dinner</strong></em></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"full_itinerary_box\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 10px; border: 1px solid rgb(235, 235, 235); font-family: Avenir, sans-serif; border-radius: 10px; background-color: rgb(253, 253, 253); float: left; width: 700px; position: relative; font-size: 14px;\">\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_title toggled\" id=\"itinerary_title_6\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 20px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; float: left; width: 678px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); cursor: pointer;\">\r\n<h2 style=\"font-style:inherit\">Day 6: Aswan Nile Cruise Tours</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_desc\" id=\"itinerary_desc_6\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 34px 20px; padding: 20px 0px 0px; border-width: 1px 0px 0px; border-top-style: solid; border-right-style: initial; border-bottom-style: initial; border-left-style: initial; border-top-color: rgb(225, 225, 225); border-right-color: initial; border-bottom-color: initial; border-left-color: initial; border-image: initial; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 15px;\">\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">After breakfast pay a visit to the High Dam, the Unfinished<a href=\"https://www.memphistours.com/Egypt/Egypt-Wikis/aswan-attractions/wiki/Unfinished-Obelisk\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(8, 149, 255); text-decoration-line: none !important;\" title=\"Unfinished Obelisk\">&nbsp;</a>Obelisk, and the majestic Philae<a href=\"https://www.memphistours.com/Egypt/Egypt-Wikis/aswan-attractions/wiki/Philae-Temple\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(8, 149, 255); text-decoration-line: none !important;\" title=\"Philae Temple\">&nbsp;</a>Temple. Enjoy lunch and dinner on board. Overnight in Aswan.<br />\r\n<em><strong>Meals: Breakfast, Lunch, Dinner</strong></em></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"full_itinerary_box\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 10px; border: 1px solid rgb(235, 235, 235); font-family: Avenir, sans-serif; border-radius: 10px; background-color: rgb(253, 253, 253); float: left; width: 700px; position: relative; font-size: 14px;\">\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_title toggled\" id=\"itinerary_title_7\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 20px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; float: left; width: 678px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); cursor: pointer;\">\r\n<h2 style=\"font-style:inherit\">Day 7: Fly Aswan to Cairo</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_desc\" id=\"itinerary_desc_7\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 34px 20px; padding: 20px 0px 0px; border-width: 1px 0px 0px; border-top-style: solid; border-right-style: initial; border-bottom-style: initial; border-left-style: initial; border-top-color: rgb(225, 225, 225); border-right-color: initial; border-bottom-color: initial; border-left-color: initial; border-image: initial; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 15px;\">\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Disembark after breakfast, free time in Aswan<a href=\"https://www.memphistours.com/Egypt/Egypt-Wikis/Egypt-Destinations/wiki/Aswan-Attractions\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(8, 149, 255); text-decoration-line: none !important;\">.</a>&nbsp;Then you will be driven to Aswan Airport for flight to Cairo<a href=\"https://www.memphistours.com/Egypt/Egypt-Wikis/Egypt-Destinations/wiki/Cairo\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(8, 149, 255); text-decoration-line: none !important;\">.</a>&nbsp;Overnight in Cairo.<br />\r\n<em><strong>Meals: Breakfast</strong></em></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"full_itinerary_box\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 10px; border: 1px solid rgb(235, 235, 235); font-family: Avenir, sans-serif; border-radius: 10px; background-color: rgb(253, 253, 253); float: left; width: 700px; position: relative; font-size: 14px;\">\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_title toggled\" id=\"itinerary_title_8\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 20px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; float: left; width: 678px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); cursor: pointer;\">\r\n<h2 style=\"font-style:inherit\">Day 8: Cairo Sightseeing Tour</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_desc\" id=\"itinerary_desc_8\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 34px 20px; padding: 20px 0px 0px; border-width: 1px 0px 0px; border-top-style: solid; border-right-style: initial; border-bottom-style: initial; border-left-style: initial; border-top-color: rgb(225, 225, 225); border-right-color: initial; border-bottom-color: initial; border-left-color: initial; border-image: initial; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 15px;\">\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Breakfast at the hotel and then you will be escorted by your private guide to visit The Egyptian<a href=\"https://www.memphistours.com/Egypt/Egypt-Wikis/Cairo-Attractions/wiki/Egyptian-Museum-Cairo\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(8, 149, 255); text-decoration-line: none !important;\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Egyptian Museum Cairo\">&nbsp;</a>Museum, where you will admire the splendid collection of Tutankhamun alongside many other fascinating artifacts. Transfer to visit Salah El Din<a href=\"https://www.memphistours.com/Egypt/Egypt-Wikis/Cairo-Attractions/wiki/Salah-El-Din-Citadel\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(8, 149, 255); text-decoration-line: none !important;\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Salah El Din Citadel\">&nbsp;</a>Citadel&nbsp;which was constructed by Salah El Din in 1183 AD to defend Cairo from the armies of Crusaders. After that visit Mohammed Ali Alabaster<a href=\"https://www.memphistours.com/Egypt/WikiTravel/Attractions-Cairo/wiki/Mohamed-Ali-Alabaster-Mosque\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(8, 149, 255); text-decoration-line: none !important;\">&nbsp;</a>Mosque, the ruler of Egypt (1805-1849) who ruled Over 45 years. Lunch will be taken in a local restaurant. Then proceed to visit Khan El Khalili&nbsp;Bazaar, one of the most famous and oldest bazaars in the Middle East. back to hotel and overnight in Cairo.<br />\r\n<em><strong>Meals: Breakfast, Lunch</strong></em></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"full_itinerary_box\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 10px; border: 1px solid rgb(235, 235, 235); font-family: Avenir, sans-serif; border-radius: 10px; background-color: rgb(253, 253, 253); float: left; width: 700px; position: relative; font-size: 14px;\">\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_title toggled\" id=\"itinerary_title_9\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 20px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; float: left; width: 678px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); cursor: pointer;\">\r\n<h2 style=\"font-style:inherit\">Day 9: Optional Excursion to Alexandria</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_desc\" id=\"itinerary_desc_9\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 34px 20px; padding: 20px 0px 0px; border-width: 1px 0px 0px; border-top-style: solid; border-right-style: initial; border-bottom-style: initial; border-left-style: initial; border-top-color: rgb(225, 225, 225); border-right-color: initial; border-bottom-color: initial; border-left-color: initial; border-image: initial; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 15px;\">\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Free day in Cairo or optional trip to&nbsp;Alexandria, to visit its famous sights, where you can see&nbsp;Qaitbay Fort, built in the 15th century by Sultan Qaitbay on the spot of Alexandria&#39;s ancient lighthouse, then move on to the new and much-acclaimed Alexandria&nbsp;Library. Also visit the Roman cemetery cut out of the rock, the Catacombs. Overnight in Cairo.<br />\r\n<strong>Meals: Breakfast</strong></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"full_itinerary_box\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 10px; border: 1px solid rgb(235, 235, 235); font-family: Avenir, sans-serif; border-radius: 10px; background-color: rgb(253, 253, 253); float: left; width: 700px; position: relative; font-size: 14px;\">\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_title toggled\" id=\"itinerary_title_10\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 20px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; float: left; width: 678px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); cursor: pointer;\">\r\n<h2 style=\"font-style:inherit\">Day 10: Cairo - Fly Back Home</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"itinerary_desc\" id=\"itinerary_desc_10\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 34px 20px; padding: 20px 0px 0px; border-width: 1px 0px 0px; border-top-style: solid; border-right-style: initial; border-bottom-style: initial; border-left-style: initial; border-top-color: rgb(225, 225, 225); border-right-color: initial; border-bottom-color: initial; border-left-color: initial; border-image: initial; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 15px;\">\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Breakfast, transfer to&nbsp;Cairo Airport&nbsp;for departure.<br />\r\n<strong><em>Meals: Breakfast</em></strong></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', '68627283_358393801776301_5140294422667198464_n.jpg', '11034199_795804730473623_3739884357963865513_n.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1940.00', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Meet and greet service by our representatives at airports&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Assistance of our guest relations during your stay</li>\r\n	<li>All transfers by a private air-conditioned vehicle</li>\r\n	<li>Accommodation for 5 nights in Cairo including breakfast &amp; taxes</li>\r\n	<li>Accommodation for 4 nights on 05 star Super deluxe Nile cruise on full board basis</li>\r\n	<li>All Sightseeing Tours in Cairo and Giza (Private Guided Tours)&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>All Sightseeing tours on your Nile Cruise (Private Guided Tours)</li>\r\n	<li>Tour to Karnak and Luxor Temples</li>\r\n	<li>Tour to Valley of the Kings, Hatshepsut temple &amp; colossi of Memnon</li>\r\n	<li>Tour to Kom Ombo and Edfu Temples</li>\r\n	<li>Tour to the High Dam, Unfinished Obelisk, Temple of Philae in Aswan</li>\r\n	<li>Entrance fees to all sites as indicated in the itinerary</li>\r\n	<li>Local English speaking guide throughout your tours</li>\r\n	<li>Lunch during tours in Cairo and Giza</li>\r\n	<li>Bottled water during the trips</li>\r\n	<li>Domestic flight (Cairo &ndash; Luxor- Aswan &ndash; Cairo)</li>\r\n	<li>Portage when needed</li>\r\n	<li>30 minutes of local calling (5 minutes international) and a mobile phone loaned for the length of your stay or an Egyptian sim card for your unlocked mobile device</li>\r\n	<li>All service charges &amp; taxes</li>\r\n</ul>', '<ul>\r\n	<li>International airfare</li>\r\n	<li>Egypt entry visa</li>\r\n	<li>Personal expenses</li>\r\n	<li>Optional activities</li>\r\n	<li>Tipping Kitty</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL, 'no', '5', NULL, 'luxury-cairo-tour-nile-cruise-giza-pyramids-packages-alexandria-egyptian-museum', NULL, NULL, '2019-08-28 16:27:29', '2019-09-02 15:34:36'),
(37, 3, 90, 'Day Tour to Luxor from Aswan', 'Day Tour to Luxor from Aswan', '<p>Drive from Aswan to Luxor by air-conditioned vehicle about 04 hours driving to visit the famous Karnak Temple the largest place of worship that was ever built.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Its ancient name Ipet-isut means &ldquo;the most sacred of places.&rdquo; The temple or more correctly (the complex of temples), was built more than two thousand years ago by different generations of pharaohs. Within the complex, the great &ldquo;Hypostyle Hall&rdquo; is an incredible forest of giant pillars.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Your Lunch would be served on the way at a local restaurant (Optional). Move on to the West Bank of the river Nile to visit the two colossal statues of Amenhotep III (Colossi of Memnon), and then you will visit the Valley of the Kings, where the magnificent tombs discovered, those tombs were carved deep into the desert rock, richly decorated and filled with treasures for the afterlife of the pharaohs, you will visit 3 tombs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Later on you will visit the Hatshepsut Temple at El Deir El Bahary, this impressive temple dedicated to Queen Hatshepsut the only female pharaoh.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Then you will have the chance to enjoy some free time at leisure in Luxor for shopping at the originals papyrus institutes and perfume places before driving back to your hotel in Aswan.</p>', '28423776_10215107494991483_229948984198543465_o.jpg', '32635786_2029653900622871_3380036736787677184_n.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '70.00', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Pick up from your hotel in Aswan and back</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">All transfers by air-conditioned vehicle</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Expert tour guide</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Entrance fees to the mentioned sights</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">All services charges and taxes</span></div>', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Any Extras</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Tipping</span></div>', NULL, 'no', '5', NULL, 'day-tour-to-luxor-from-aswan', NULL, NULL, '2019-08-28 16:38:24', '2019-09-02 15:37:53'),
(38, 3, 89, 'Hot Air Balloon Ride in Luxor, Egypt', '45 minutes ride in Hot Air Balloon, in the sky of Luxor', '<p>Early morning,<span style=\"color:#0000FF\"><span style=\"font-family:helvetica,arial,sans-serif\">Signature Tours Egypt</span></span> representative will pick you up from your hotel in Luxor to the West Bank to enjoy air balloon riding. Transfer to marine enjoy Soft drinks before you take the motor boat to the west bank , then you will be transferred to the take off area where you are going to start your balloon ride in the sky of the biggest open-air museum (Luxor).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The &ldquo;Balloon Ride&rdquo; trip departs everyday, however confirmation in advance is still highly recommended.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The balloon ride takes 45 minutes, before your land again, to catch your pick-up and return to your hotel.</p>', '1451379_265727113575257_421693095_n.jpg', '10371922_676057529131968_4007260189544072968_n.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '100.00', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Pick up Service from your hotel &amp; return</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Transfer by air conditioned bus</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Motor boat to transfer to the West Bank</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">45 minutes ride in Hot Air Balloon, in the sky of Luxor</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Flight certificate</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">All service charges and taxes</span></div>', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Any extras not mentioned in the program</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Tipping</span></div>', NULL, 'no', '5', NULL, 'hot-air-balloon-ride-in-luxor-egypt', NULL, NULL, '2019-08-30 10:11:52', '2019-09-02 15:40:02'),
(39, 3, 89, 'Abu Simbel and Aswan Tour from Luxor', 'Abu Simbel and Aswan Tour from Luxor', '<h3><em><strong><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">From the moment your tour starts, your guide will give you full attention. Once in the car, your guide will talk to you about all the things on the way as well as other aspects of your tour that will interest you.</span></strong></em></h3>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong><span style=\"font-size:16px\">Day 1: Luxor to Aswan Sightseeing Tours</span></strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>07:00 AM you will be met and assisted at your hotel in Luxor and transferred to Aswan (approx. 03 hours and half per way) for a wonderful tour to visit the majestic Philae Temple which was built on the honor of Goddess Isis the chief deity of the island, lunch at local restaurant in Aswan included, and then enjoy a motor boat riding to the Nubian Village which situated at the bottom of Elephantine Island to discover the simple and natural life of the very kind and hospitable Nubian people finally you will be transferred to your hotel in Aswan for check-in with free time at leisure and overnight stay</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Meals: Lunch</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Day 2: Safari Trip at Abu Simbel</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Breakfast will be provided by hotel in Aswan, and then 10:00 AM you will be accompanied by your guide and driver to Abu Simbel for about 03 hours drive. As soon as you arrive, you will start your Safari Trip from Shokan mount about 15 KM from Abu Simbel with 2 stops taking some photos for Sphinx and Shitan Mountains. As soon as we arrive to Shokan Mountain, trekking for 2 KM till arrive to the lake. Ride the boat and enjoy the scenery of the natural view of the lake with taking some photos to Abu Simbel temples and Bird Mountain which called The White Mountain. Back to stay that night at hotel.</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\">Optional Sound &amp; Light Show at Abu Simbel Temples</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\">Meals : Breakfast, Lunch</div>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Day 3: Abu Simbel Temples</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>After breakfast at hotel, you will be check out then pay a visit the two Temples of Abu Simbel, with their unique style, are considered to be the masterpieces of ancient Egypt. They reflect the glory and grandeur of the new Kingdom. The Egyptian government and UNESCO decided to co-operate in order to save these temples from the flood.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Temple of Ramsses II was dedicated to the four universal gods Ptah, Re-Her-Akhtey, Amun-Re, and to Ramsses II himself. The great Abu Simbel temple is also called The Sun Temple of Ramssess II.The Temple of Queen Nefertari is also Called Temple of Hathor who was the wife of the Sun God so in a symbolic way, the two Temples, that of Ramsses II and that of Nefertari, king Ramesses II, Nefertari, Hathor and the Sun God together as one.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Lunch at local restaurant in Aswan,&nbsp;Travel in comfort back to your hotel, Luxor&nbsp;has so much to see, feel, eat and buy so if you have time and want to add more to your itinerary &ndash; just let us know what you are interested in and we will arrange it for you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Meals: Breakfast, Lunch</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '61653626_707095809745685_8707724031438094336_n.jpg', '50026295_10155861300301466_4308231001118605312_n.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '460.00', '<h3><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Pick up service from your hotel in Luxor and return</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Expert tour guide</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Accommodation for 01 night in Movenpick Aswan Resort including breakfast</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Accommodation for 01 night in Seti Hotel Abu Simbel including breakfast</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Lunch meals during tours to Aswan and Abu Simbel</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Entrance fees to the mentioned historical sights</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">All transfers by modern air-conditioning vehicle</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">All service charges and taxes included</span></h3>', '<h3><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Optional activities</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Personal spending</span><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Tipping</span></h3>', NULL, 'no', '5', NULL, 'abu-simbel-and-aswan-tour-from-luxor-bird-mountain-queen-nefertari-king-ramesses-ii-nefertari-hathor-and-the-sun-god', NULL, NULL, '2019-08-30 10:50:53', '2019-09-02 15:45:32');
