(52, 3, 93, 'St. Catherine Trip', 'Set out from Sharm El Sheikh to explore Sinai. First you will visit St. Catherine Monastery, the oldest working Christian monasteries in the world..', '<p style=\"direction: ltr; \">Early morning <span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 255)\">Signature Tours Egypt</span> representative will pick you up from your hotel to discover the top highlights of Sinai desert.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr; \">We drive to Saint Catherine monastery located in heart of Sinai Peninsula at a height of 1570 meters in the place where according to the tradition Moses saw the bush on fire which didn&rsquo;t burn up.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">It is in the foot hills of Gable Moses or mount Sinai,on whose summit Moses received the tables of the law with the ten commandments inscribed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">The monastery dates back to the age of the emperor Justinian 6th century. it was the same time of building enclosure wall surrounding the monastery right now but The monastery was named saint Catherine at the beginning of the 11th century in honor of saint Catherine, one of the earliest Alexandria Christians martyrs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">Then drive back to you hotel.</p>', '1510520_821983757872882_6457995737581573025_n.jpg', '39846773_10156661980038410_6769174483505774592_o.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '65.00', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Pick up services from your hotel in Sharm and return</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Tour guide</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">All taxes &amp; service charge</span></div>', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Any extras not mentioned in the program</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Tipping Kitty</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Personal expenses</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Optional activities</span></div>', NULL, 'no', '5', NULL, 'st-catherine-trip-emperor-justinian', NULL, NULL, '2019-08-30 13:39:50', '2019-09-03 11:09:11'),
(53, 3, 93, 'Dahab Safari & Snorkeling at Blue Hole', 'Venture out from Dahab in a 4x4 and head to the protected area of Abu Galoum. Enjoy a camel ride and snorkeling at this pristine, remote reef. Experience snorkeling at the famous Blue Hole.', '<p style=\"direction: ltr; \">Our experienced drivers will transfer you in air-conditioned jeeps into the desert to see the Bedouins and their villages, with opportunity to enjoy Tea with them.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">Then move on to Dahab to visit Wadi Qunai which is an oasis with palm trees and a small sandstone canyon. Then take the camel from the Bedouin villages to compare four wheels with four legs as you travel like a local on an unforgettable camel ride.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">The camels led you to snorkel at the famous Blue Hole completes the activates for the day. Later on you will be driven to Dahab to enjoy lunch at a local restaurant before driving by the jeep back to your hotel in Sharm El Sheikh.</p>', '969787466_Borut-Furlan-4_800x531.jpg', '11887990_1047317398626475_7598701788161557143_n.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '65.00', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Pick up services from your hotel in Sharm El Sheikh and return</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">All transfers by 4&times;4 Jeep</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Tour guide</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Snorkeling equipments</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Lunch during your trip</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Mineral water on board the Jeep</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">All service charges &amp; taxes</span></div>', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Any extras not mentioned in the program</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Tipping Kitty</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Personal expenses</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Optional activities</span></div>', NULL, 'no', '5', NULL, 'dahab-safari-snorkeling-at-blue-hole', NULL, NULL, '2019-08-30 14:04:53', '2019-09-02 14:57:33'),
(54, 3, 93, 'Day Trip to Cairo from Sharm by Air', 'Fly to Cairo and take in the Giza Pyramids and the Sphinx and then visit the Egypt Museum to see the world‚Äôs largest collection of Ancient Egyptian artifacts. Go shopping in Khan El Khalil, Cairo famous bazaar, before returning to Sharm El Sheikh.', '<p style=\"direction: ltr; \">Panorama Egypt Tours representative will pick you up from your hotel in Sharm El Sheikh &amp; transfer to Sharm Airport to Fly to Cairo, where you will be met &amp; assissted by our Cairo representative.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">After that our tour guide will accompany you to discover the exquisite Pyramids of Cheops, Chephren and Mykerinus, the Sphinx with a head of a pharaoh and lion&rsquo;s body, which dates back to the reign of King Chephren, and the Valley Temple of the Pyramid of Chephren.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">Proceed to have your (Optional) lunch at local resturant in Cairo. Then we will move on to the&nbsp;<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Egyptian Museum</span>&nbsp;which features artifacts from the Pharaonic period.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">The museum displays a rare collection of 5000 years of art which is considered the largest most precious collection of Egyptian art in the world.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">Over 250,000 genuine artifacts are presented, including an exhibit dedicated to Tutankhamen collection of treasure, gold and jewelry which was enclosed in his tomb for over 3,500 years before it was discovered in the 1920s when his tomb was excavated. Shopping at Khan El Khalili Bazaar, the most famous bazaar in the Middle east.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr; \">In the evening you will be driven to Cairo Airport for flight back to Sharm.</p>', '65260856_10156720110924541_6880793738566696960_n.jpg', '14205919_1213217118719594_971544518224347532_o.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '280.00', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Pick up services from your hotel in Sharm and return</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">All transfers by air-conditioned vehicle</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Return flight ticket Sharm / Cairo / Sharm</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Tour guide during your trip</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Entrance fees to the mentioned sites in Cairo</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">All taxes &amp; service charge</span></div>', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Any extras not mentioned in the itinerary</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Tipping</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Personal spending</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Optional activities</span></div>', NULL, 'no', '5', NULL, 'egyptian-museum-pyramids-of-cheops-chephren-and-mykerinus-the-sphinx-tutankhamen', NULL, '2019-08-30 14:25:41', '2019-08-30 14:20:53', '2019-08-30 14:25:41'),
(55, 3, 93, 'Day Trip to Cairo from Sharm by Air', 'Fly to Cairo and take in the Giza Pyramids and the Sphinx and then visit the Egypt Museum to see the world‚Äôs largest collection of Ancient Egyptian artifacts. Go shopping in Khan El Khalil, Cairo famous bazaar, before returning to Sharm El Sheikh.', '<p>Panorama Egypt Tours representative will pick you up from your hotel in Sharm El Sheikh &amp; transfer to Sharm Airport to Fly to Cairo, where you will be met &amp; assissted by our Cairo representative.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After that our tour guide will accompany you to discover the exquisite Pyramids of Cheops, Chephren and Mykerinus, the Sphinx with a head of a pharaoh and lion&rsquo;s body, which dates back to the reign of King Chephren, and the Valley Temple of the Pyramid of Chephren.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Proceed to have your (Optional) lunch at local resturant in Cairo. Then we will move on to the&nbsp;<span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Egyptian Museum</span>&nbsp;which features artifacts from the Pharaonic period.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The museum displays a rare collection of 5000 years of art which is considered the largest most precious collection of Egyptian art in the world.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Over 250,000 genuine artifacts are presented, including an exhibit dedicated to Tutankhamen collection of treasure, gold and jewelry which was enclosed in his tomb for over 3,500 years before it was discovered in the 1920s when his tomb was excavated. Shopping at Khan El Khalili Bazaar, the most famous bazaar in the Middle east.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the evening you will be driven to Cairo Airport for flight back to Sharm.</p>', '65260856_10156720110924541_6880793738566696960_n.jpg', '14205919_1213217118719594_971544518224347532_o.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '280.00', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Pick up services from your hotel in Sharm and return</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\