(96, 3, 86, 'White Desert and Bahariya Oasis Tour From Cairo', 'Enjoy Bahariya Oasis Tour in the Western Desert, then head to the surrounding desert to watch the unique regions known as the Black and White Deserts in a breathtaking experience that will mark your stay in Egypt.', '<div style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-family: Avenir, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">\r\n<p><strong>Day 1: Cairo To Baharyia Oasis by car / White Desert Tour</strong><br />\r\nEarly morning your tour guide will pick you up from your hotel in Cairo and transfer you to Bahariya<a href=\"https://www.memphistours.com/Egypt/Egypt-Wikis/oases-and-the-western-desert/wiki/Baharia-Oasis\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(8, 149, 255); text-decoration-line: none !important;\">&nbsp;</a>Oasis&nbsp;about 360 km east Cairo&nbsp;this journey takes about 4 hours, Having lunch upon reaching Bahariya Oasis. Then continue to visit The Black<a href=\"https://www.memphistours.com/Egypt/WikiTravel/the-western-desert-and-oases/wiki/Black-desert-\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(8, 149, 255); text-decoration-line: none !important;\">&nbsp;</a>Desert&nbsp;and the natural hot spring of El<a href=\"https://www.memphistours.com/Egypt/WikiTravel/the-western-desert-and-oases/wiki/Valley-of-Al-Haiz\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(8, 149, 255); text-decoration-line: none !important;\">&nbsp;</a>Haize&nbsp;( St.George Oasis ), then drive to see the quartz crystal at Crystal<a href=\"https://www.memphistours.com/Egypt/WikiTravel/the-western-desert-and-oases/wiki/The-Crystal-Mountain\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(8, 149, 255); text-decoration-line: none !important;\">&nbsp;</a>Mountain, and the rocky formations in the Valley of Agabat.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Continue driving to The White<a href=\"https://www.memphistours.com/Egypt/WikiTravel/the-western-desert-and-oases/wiki/White-Desert\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(8, 149, 255); text-decoration-line: none !important;\">&nbsp;</a>Desert&nbsp;National Park the most well-known desert destination in Egypt&nbsp;for a good reason. The quantity of unearthly and beautiful wind-carved rock formations shaped in the form of giant mushrooms or pebbles is unequalled in any desert in the world. Then Camp in the white desert or overnight at Farafra oasis hotel according to the possibility .<br />\r\n<strong>Meals: Lunch, Dinner</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-family: Avenir, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">\r\n<p><strong>Day 02: Bahariya Oasis Tour / Drive Back To Cairo</strong><br />\r\nBreakfast at the campsite then drive to Bahariya<a href=\"https://www.memphistours.com/Egypt/Egypt-Wikis/oases-and-the-western-desert/wiki/Baharia-Oasis\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(8, 149, 255); text-decoration-line: none !important;\" target=\"_blank\">&nbsp;</a>Oasis&nbsp;to visit the golden mummy show room and nobles tombs ( 2 tombs ) from the 26<span style=\"font-family:inherit; font-size:10.5px\">th</span>&nbsp;dynasty, that is a huge burial site at Bahariya<a href=\"https://www.memphistours.com/Egypt/Egypt-Wikis/oases-and-the-western-desert/wiki/Baharia-Oasis\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(8, 149, 255); text-decoration-line: none !important;\" target=\"_blank\">&nbsp;</a>Oasis&nbsp;in The Western Desert of<a href=\"https://www.memphistours.com/Egypt/Egypt-Wikis/Egypt-Destinations/wiki/The-Western-Desert-and-Oases\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; background-color: transparent; color: rgb(8, 149, 255); text-decoration-line: none !important;\">&nbsp;</a>Egypt&nbsp;and the Tomb of Bannantiu in the Bahariya Oasis. Then you will enjoy climbing the Black Mountain. Enjoy your lunch at Bahariya oasis&nbsp;before driving back to Cairo.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Meals: Breakfast, Lunch</strong></p>\r\n</div>', '26def_White_Desert_1-1.jpg', '1200px-White_desert.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '115.00', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Pick up services from hotel &amp; return</li>\r\n	<li>Entrance fees to the mentioned historical place</li>\r\n	<li>Transfer by a private air-conditioned vehicle</li>\r\n	<li>Transfer by a private 4 X 4 vehicle to the white and Black Deserts</li>\r\n	<li>Accommodation 1 night in desert camping</li>\r\n	<li>1 Breakfast meal, 2 Lunch meals and 1 Dinner meal</li>\r\n	<li>Bottled water during your trip</li>\r\n	<li>Desert Expert</li>\r\n	<li>All taxes &amp; service charge</li>\r\n</ul>', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Any extras not mentioned in the program</li>\r\n	<li>Tipping</li>\r\n	<li>Personal spendings</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL, 'no', '1', NULL, 'white-desert-and-bahariya-oasis-tour-from-cairo-egypt-tours-white-and-black-desert-tour', 6, NULL, '2019-09-01 11:11:20', '2019-09-03 13:51:09'),
(97, 3, 89, 'Trip to Kharga and Dakhla Oases from Luxor', 'Trip to Kharga and Dakhla Oases from Luxor', '<h3 style=\"direction: ltr; \">Day 01:- Luxor to Kharga Oasis &ndash; Dakhla Oasis</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">05:30 A.M. <span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 255)\">Signature Tours Egypt</span> guide will pick you up from your hotel in Luxor to drive to El Kharga Oasis, about 05 hours driving to visit the Roman Temple of Hibis &amp; Nadora from outside and the early Christian Cemetery with its chapels painted with murals at Bagawat.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr; \">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\">Then we drive to Dakhla Oasis, where we spend the night at an Oasis style hut with reed huts, communal showers and basic facilities. Overnight in Dakhla.</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\">Meals: Lunch, Dinner</div>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"direction: ltr;\">Day 2: Dakhla Oasis to Kharga Oasis</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\">After breakfast, enjoy a trip to the Roman temple of Deir El Hagar in its serene surroundings and the Roman burial ground Mezzawaqqa. Then pay a visit to Islamic Village of Al Qasr, about 35km from Mut, houses ruins of an Ayubid mosque. Then transfer to Kharga and overnight camping in Kharga Oasis.</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\">Meals: Breakfast, Lunch, Dinner</div>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"direction: ltr;\">Day 3: Kharga Oasis to Luxor</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">Breakfast at the campsite, Travel in comfort back to your hotel, Luxor&nbsp;has so much to see, feel, eat and buy so if you have time and want to add more to your itinerary &ndash; just let us know what you are interested in and we will arrange it for you.</p>', '26991777_1320319471447164_8061893570949777770_n.jpg', '848489288_5D-Bedouin-tea.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '400.00', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; fo