(99, 3, 92, 'Trip To Cairo from Alexandria', 'Trip To Cairo from Alexandria\r\nThe Great pyramids \r\nThe Sphinx \r\nThe Egyptian Museum', '<p style=\"direction: ltr; \"><strong>From the moment your tour starts, your&nbsp;</strong><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 255)\">Signature Tours Egypt</span><strong> guides will give you full attention. Once in the car, your guide will talk to you about all the things on the way as well as other aspects of your tour that will interest you.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\"><strong>Travel to the&nbsp;Great Pyramids&nbsp;one of the Seven Wonders of the Ancient World, enjoy a&nbsp;panoramic view of the Pyramids of Cheops, Chephren, and&nbsp;Mykerinus. Visit The Great Sphinx, the Valley Temple &amp;&nbsp; many outstanding photo stops.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\"><strong>Move on to visit the&nbsp;Museum of Egyptian Antiquities&nbsp;that includes King Tutankhamen&rsquo;s treasures.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr; \"><strong>End the day with an optional visit to traditional bazaars then drive&nbsp;back to Alexandria.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\"><strong>Your day trip to Cairo has been designed to help you enjoy the maximum amount of Cairo&nbsp;with the least amount of time.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\"><strong>If you want to&nbsp;customize&nbsp;your trip, please let us know.</strong></p>', '1508060_1022264127849835_1660362789188418642_n.jpg', '12974299_604180619763552_2430542606341012240_n.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '50.00', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">* Pick up services from Alexandria &amp; return</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">* All transfers by a private air-conditioned vehicle</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">* Expert tour guide</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">* Entrance fees to all the mentioned sites</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">* All Service charges &amp; taxes</span></div>', '<p style=\"direction: ltr; \"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">* Any extras not mentioned</span></p>', NULL, 'no', '5', NULL, 'the-great-pyramids-the-sphinx-the-egyptian-museum', 9, NULL, '2019-09-01 11:52:38', '2019-09-03 13:51:09'),
(100, 3, 99, '5 Days Cairo Tour Package', '5 Days Cairo Tour Package', '<h3 style=\"direction: ltr; \"><strong>Day 1:Arrival Cairo</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr; \">Arrival to Cairo airport, Upon you arrival you will find our representative waiting you with the sign of <span style=\"color:#0000FF\">Signature Tours Egypt</span>, then you will be transferred by an accessible air-conditioned modern van adapted for wheelchair travelers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">Panorama Egypt tours representative will assist with a smooth check-in and review your holiday itinerary with you to establish and confirm pick-up times for each tour. Overnight in Cairo.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"direction: ltr;\"><strong>Day 2:Pyramids / Memphis</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">Breakfast at your hotel in Cairo and then met by your <span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 255)\">Signature Tours Egypt</span> guide who will accompany you to Giza Plateau to visit one of the seven wonders of the ancient world, the Great Pyramids of Cheops, Chefren and Mykerinus, famous Sphinx and Valley temple facing the great statue.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">All places are wheelchair accessible. (Optional) Lunch will be served at a good quality restaurant in Cairo.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">Move on to visit Memphis; the ancient capital of Egypt, then back to your hotel and overnight in Cairo.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"direction: ltr;\"><strong>Day 3:Museum / Citadel</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">After Breakfast, move on to the Egyptian Museum, with a well-paved site for wheelchair travelers, where you can see the magnificent collection of Tutankhamen, among many other fascinating pharaonic artifacts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">Lunch at a good quality restaurant, then move on to visit the Citadel of Salah El Din and Mohamed Ali Alabaster Mosque in Islamic Cairo, both including well-paved sites for wheelchair travelers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">Overnight in Cairo.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"direction: ltr;\"><strong>Day 4:Optional Alexandria</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 255)\">Signature Tours Egypt</span> guide will pick you up from your hotel to start your tour to Alexandria. Start the tour with the library of Alexandria; the biggest library in the world &ndash; now with 8 million books. Visit it&rsquo;s open court and free museums.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">Note: Alexandria Library is closed on Fridays and on every public holiday. To enter the reading area you will need to purchase an extra ticket.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">Then visit the Site of the Lighthouse; one of the Seven Wonders of the Ancient World on which now stands the castle of Qaitbey. Visit the royal gardens of King Farouk (the last king in the history of Egypt) and see the royal palaces of Haramlek and Salamlek as well as the royal beaches of the queens. Continue your tour by visiting the prettiest and biggest mosque in the city: the Abbo Elabbas Mosque, as well as the memorial of the Unknown Soldier of Alexandria and the statue of Alexander the Great.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">You can then stop for lunch (Optional) before visiting the church of St. Mark &ndash; the oldest church in Africa before driving along the Cornish (30 km) to see the whole city of Alexandria from the sea side which includes the old harbor of Alexandria where we found 7000 monuments underwater. Stop over the famous bridge of Stanley &ndash; the modern landmark of modern Alexandria, before visiting the old downtown of Alexandria and walking through the old city-center of Alexandria: built by Alexander the great. Travel in comfort back to your hotel.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">Alexandria has so much to see, feel, eat and buy so if you have time and want to add more to your itinerary &ndash; just let us know what you are interested in and we will arrange it for you at the cost price &ndash; no profit to us. Back to your hotel in Cairo.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"direction: ltr;\"><strong>Day 5:Final Departure</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">After breakfast, you will be driven by an wheelchair accessible modern vehicle to Cairo International Airport for final departure.</p>', '37322664_1888523594503464_2929397596881420288_n.jpg', '37283746_1888523587836798_6451096025972080640_n.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '350.00', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Meet and greet service by our representatives at airport</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Assistance of our guest relations during your stay</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Accommodation for 4 nights in Cairo including breakfast</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Entrance fees to all sites as indicated in the itinerary</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Expert tour guide</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">All transfers by an adapted A/C vehicle</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Meals in hotel and during tours as indicated in the itinerary</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Portage when needed</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">All service charges and taxes</span></div>', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Visa; We can provide you with your visa upon arrival at your request.</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">International Flights</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Personal items.</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Tipping.</span></div>', NULL, 'no', '5', NULL, 'giza-pyramids-cairo-museum-alexandria-library-sphinx', 10, NULL, '2019-09-01 13:01:21', '2019-09-03 14:49:54'),
(101, 3, 99, '10 Days Cairo, Luxor and Hurghada', '10 Days Cairo, Luxor and Hurghada', '<h3 style=\"direction: ltr; \">Day 1:Arrival Cairo</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">Arrival to Cairo airport, Upon you arrival you will find our representative waiting you with the sign of Panorama <span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 255)\">Signature Tours Egypt</span>, then you will be transferred by an accessible air-conditioned modern van adapted for wheelchair travelers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 255)\">Signature Tours Egypt</span> representative will assist with a smooth check-in and review your holiday itinerary with you to establish and confirm pick-up times for each tour. Overnight in Cairo.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"direction: ltr; \">Day 2:Pyramids / Museum</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">Breakfast at your hotel in Cairo and then your personal guide will pick you up by an accessible air-conditioned modern van and accompany you to Giza Plateau to visit one of the seven wonders of the ancient world, the Great Pyramids of Cheops, Chefren and Mykerinus, famous Sphinx and Valley temple facing the great statue.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">All places are wheelchair accessible. (Optional) Lunch will be served at a good quality restaurant. Then move onto the Egyptian Museum, well-paved place, where you can see the collection of Tutankhamen among other splendid pharaonic artifacts. Then transfer to your hotel. Overnight in Cairo.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"direction: ltr;\">Day 3:Optional Alexandria</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 255)\">Signature Tours Egypt</span> guide will pick you up from your hotel to start your tour to Alexandria. Start the tour with the library of Alexandria; the biggest library in the world &ndash; now with 8 million books. Visit it&rsquo;s open court and free museums.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">Note: Alexandria Library is closed on Fridays and on every public holiday. To enter the reading area you will need to purchase an extra ticket.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">Then visit the Site of the Lighthouse; one of the Seven Wonders of the Ancient World on which now stands the castle of Qaitbey. Visit the royal gardens of King Farouk (the last king in the history of Egypt) and see the royal palaces of Haramlek and Salamlek as well as the royal beaches of the queens. Continue your tour by visiting the prettiest and biggest mosque in the city: the Abbo Elabbas Mosque, as well as the memorial of the Unknown Soldier of Alexandria and the statue of Alexander the Great.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">You can then stop for lunch (Optional) before visiting the church of St. Mark &ndash; the oldest church in Africa before driving along the Cornish (30 km) to see the whole city of Alexandria from the sea side which includes the old harbor of Alexandria where we found 7000 monuments underwater.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">Stop over the famous bridge of Stanley &ndash; the modern landmark of modern Alexandria, before visiting the old downtown of Alexandria and walking through the old city-center of Alexandria: built by Alexander the great. Travel in comfort back to your hotel.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">Alexandria has so much to see, feel, eat and buy so if you have time and want to add more to your itinerary &ndash; just let us know what you are interested in and we will arrange it for you at the cost price &ndash; no profit to us. Back to Cairo.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"direction: ltr;\">Day 4:Cairo/ Luxor West Bank</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">Breakfast, check out from your hotel in Cairo, then you will be transferred to Cairo Airport for a flight to Luxor where you will be met and assisted by our representative at the airport. Check in at your Luxor Hotel, provided by accessible facilities for wheelchair travelers, then your tour guide will escort you to the west bank, to see the Temple of Queen Hatshepsut and the Colossi of Memnon. Overnight in Luxor.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"direction: ltr;\">Day 5:Luxor East Bank</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">Breakfast at your hotel in Luxor, then move to visit the magnificent Karnak and Luxor Temples on the east bank of Luxor. Back to your hotel and overnight in Luxor.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"direction: ltr;\">Day 6 :Luxor/ Hurghada</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">You will be transferred from Luxor to Hurghada on the Red Sea by an accessible modern air-conditioned vehicle (about 04 hours driving) where you will be moved to your Resort at Hurghada, enjoying disabled accessible services during your stay.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"direction: ltr;\">Day 7 :Hurghada</h3>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\">Free Day in Hurghada</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\">Meals: Breakfast</div>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"direction: ltr;\">Day 8:Hurghada</h3>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\">Free Day in Hurghada</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\">Meals: Breakfast</div>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"direction: ltr;\">Day 9:Back Cairo</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">Transfer to Hurghada Airport by an accessible private air-conditioned modern van for flight to Cairo. Upon your arrival at Cairo Airport, you will be driven to the area of Islamic Cairo, where you will be able to explore Cairo&rsquo;s old bazaar. Then drive to your hotel in Cairo. Overnight in Cairo.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"direction: ltr;\">Day 10:Final Departure</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">After breakfast, you will be transferred by an accessible modern van to Cairo International Airport for final departure.</p>', '14344902_1090098037752313_4765739140385715133_n.jpg', '69158096_1069605803242018_2440196114582863872_n.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1000.00', '<p style=\"direction: ltr; \"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Meet and greet service by our representatives at airport</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr; \"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Assistance of our guest relations during your stay</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr; \"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Accommodation in Cairo for 04 nights</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr; \"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Accommodation in Luxor for 02 nights</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr; \"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Accommodation in Hurghada for 03 night</span></p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Domestic flight (Cairo &ndash; Luxor &ndash; Hurghada &ndash; Cairo)</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Entrance fees to all sites as indicated in the itinerary</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Expert tour guide</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">All transfers by an adapted A/C vehicle</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Meals in hotel and during tours as indicated in the itinerary</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Portage when needed</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">All service charges and taxes</span></div>', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Visa; We can provide you with your visa upon arrival at your request.</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">International Flights</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Personal items.</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Tipping.</span></div>', NULL, 'no', '5', NULL, 'cairo-luxor-hurghada', 11, NULL, '2019-09-01 13:17:16', '2019-09-03 14:54:53'),
(102, 3, 99, '8 Days Cairo and Nile Cruise Tour', 'Cairo and Nile Cruise Tour', '<h3 style=\"direction: ltr; \">Day 1:Arrival Cairo</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">Arrival to Cairo airport, Upon you arrival you will find our&nbsp;representative waiting you with the sign of <span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 255)\">Signature Tours Egypt</span>, then you will be transferred by an accessible air-conditioned modern van adapted for wheelchair travelers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 255)\">Signature Tours Egypt</span> representative will assist with a smooth check-in and review your holiday itinerary with you to establish and confirm pick-up times for each tour. Overnight in Cairo.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"direction: ltr; \">Day 2:Pyramids / Museum</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">Breakfast at your hotel in Cairo and then met by your personal guide who will accompany you to Giza Plateau to visit one of the seven wonders of the ancient world, the Great Pyramids of Cheops, Chefren and Mykerinus, famous Sphinx and Valley temple facing the great statue.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">All places are wheelchair accessible. (Optional) Lunch will be served at a good quality restaurant. Then move onto the Egyptian Museum, well-paved place, where you can see the collection of Tutankhamen among other splendid pharaonic artifacts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">Continue driving to Islamic Cairo, where you will be able to explore Khan El Khalili, Cairo&rsquo;s old bazaar. Overnight in Cairo.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"direction: ltr;\">Day 3:Cairo/ Luxor East Bank</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">After Breakfast, check out from your hotel in Cairo, then, you will be transferred to Cairo Airport for departure to Luxor where you will be met and assisted, then taken by a wheelchair accessible air-conditioned vehicle to board your 5 star deluxe cruise boat for wheelchair (disabled) travelers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">After lunch on board, enjoy a visit to the impressive Karnak and Luxor Temples. Dinner and overnight on board.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"direction: ltr;\">Day 4:Luxor West Bank/ Edfu</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">After breakfast on your Nile cruise, take an excursion to mortuary Temple of Queen Hatshepsut, which was built by the architects of the New Kingdom Pharaoh Hatshepsut approximately in the 15th century BC.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">Proceeding to the Colossi of Memnon. After lunch, you will sail to Edfu enjoying a leisurely dinner on board. Overnight on board Nile Cruise.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"direction: ltr;\">Day 5:Edfu / Kom Ombo Temples</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">After breakfast on Nile Cruise, visit the well-preserved Ptolemaic Temple dedicated to Horus at Edfu. Sail to Kom Ombo to see the unique Temple of Sobek, dedicated to Sobek the crocodile god, and Horus the falcon-headed god. Lunch on board. Continue sailing to Aswan. Dinner and overnight on board you deluxe Nile Cruise.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"direction: ltr;\">Day 6:Aswan Sightseeing</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">Enjoy a day&rsquo;s sightseeing in Aswan. Start with the High Dam, then move on to visit the Nubian Village by an accessible van. Dinner and overnight on board.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"direction: ltr;\">Day 7:Back to Cairo</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">Transfer to Aswan airport to return to Cairo, where you&rsquo;ll be met and assisted at the airport, then you will be transferred to your hotel. Overnight in Cairo.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"direction: ltr;\">Day 8:Final Departure</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"direction: ltr;\">After enjoying a beautiful breakfast, you will be transferred by a wheelchair accessible modern vehicle to Cairo International Airport for final departure.</p>', '18157127_770723683103806_1437775353739500385_n.jpg', '67578385_1722549094558482_3678531200013565952_n.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '900.00', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Meet and greet service by our representatives at airport</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Assistance of our guest relations during your stay</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Accommodation for 3 nights in Cairo including breakfast</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Accommodation for 4 nights on 5* deluxe Nile cruise full board</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Domestic flight (Cairo &ndash; Luxor- Aswan &ndash; Cairo)</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Entrance fees to all sites as indicated in the itinerary</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Expert tour guide</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">All transfers by an adapted A/C vehicle</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Meals in hotel and during tours as indicated in the itinerary</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Portage when needed</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">All service charges and taxes</span></div>', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Visa; We can provide you with your visa upon arrival at your request</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">International Flights</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Personal items</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"direction: ltr;\"><span style=\"font-family:montserratregular; font-size:16px\">Tipping</span></div>', NULL, 'no', '5', NULL, 'cairo-luxor-aswan', 12, NULL, '2019-09-01 13:36:26', '2019-09-03 14:58:55');
